Commentary: Some action straightaway! A huge appeal but turned down! A little too high probably. Broad lands this outside off, it is on a length. He usually takes the ball away from around the wicket but this time gets it toÂ  jag back in. Warner makes a leave probably thinking it would move away. He gets hit high on the pads. An appeal from the slip cordon and Broad too who is down on the ground. Turned down. Broad signals it is too high.
Slightly fuller this time and on middle, Warner defends it nicely.
Another one on a length and just outside off, Warner covers his off pole and shoulders arms to this one.
Good delivery! Broad goes fuller, enticing the batter to drive. Warner does go for it, this one comes back in a little, it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
Length agian and on off, this lands and moves away. It also seems like it stuck in the surface, it just about gets to Sam Billings.

A maiden then to begin with by Broad! On off, this is pushed to covers. So not a lot of movement for the pacer but we saw one ball zip through and the other just hold in the surface in the first over.
That is a beauty to begin with by Ollie Robinson! This is on a length and around off, it lands and moves away. Usman Khawaja is beaten as he tries to block.

Another good delivery! Length and on off, this one also lands and moves away. Khawaja is once again beaten as he tries to block. Robinson has got to get the ball moving off the wicket in his first two deliveries, he has started off well here.
On middle, this time Khawaja gets right behind the line of the delivery and keeps it out.

Australia and Usman Khawaja are underway! Full and on middle, Khawaja clips it through square leg and takes two. Robinson went a little too full there and it was easy pickings for a man who scored two tons in the last game.
Now drags his length back and bowls it on middle, no movement this time, Khawaja stays back and plays it back to the bowler.
Two from Robinson's first then! Length and just outside off, Khawaja shoulders arms to this one.
Just outside off, Warner covers his off pole and leaves it alone.
Loose! Short and wide outside off, Warner slashes well away from his body, gets beaten. Too early probably to play that shot.

Close! Not sure why Broad was appealing there! Length and on off, this one skids through. Warner is a touch late in getting his bat down. It hits the underedge and bounces just in front of the stumps and then goes over it.
Testing stuff from Broad here! Now goes for the yorker, looks to catch Warner by surprise. David gets his bat down and jams it out.
Goes back to bowling it on a length and outside off, left alone.
Another maiden for Broad! England have started well. Length and on off, Warner plays it to point.
Very stylish but for no runs! Fuller and on middle, Khawaja flicks but to mid-wicket.
Just outside off, angling away. Khawaja moves across and lets it be.
Cramps the batter for room by bowling it on his body. Khawaja looks to flick but misses to get hit on the body.
Another one outside off, Khawaja does not fiddle with it.

Good nut! Need to start it a little straighter, this lands just outside off, it pitches and moves away. Khawaja is beaten as he tires to defend. There was quite some distance between the edge and the ball.
Better! A near perfect delivery. It lands on off and then moves away. Squares Khawaja up as he tries to block. It whizzes past the outside edge.
On middle, slightly fuller, this is flicked but to mid-wicket.
Down the leg side this time, Warner looks to work it on the leg side but misses.
Yet again on the fuller side, no movement in the air, Warner plays it to mid on.
A little too straight, Warner looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. Leg bye taken. Warner is yet to get off the mark.
On middle, Khawaja stays back and blocks.
BEAUTY! Gets this to move away nicely. Fuller, just behind a driving length. Khawaja is tempted into a drive. The ball though lands and then moves away. Beats the outside edge.
Outside off, moving away. Warner watches it go to the keeper. A lot of patience shown by the Aussie openers so far and rightly so. They need to get past this tough phase.
This lands just outside leg, holds its line. Warner stays back and tries to block but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Good length and on off, Warner plays it to covers.
Just outside off, Warner does not fiddle with it.
On middle, Warner lunges and defends. The openers have done well so far. Worrying signs for England though that they have not got a wicket yet. The good thing is they have not gone for a lot of runs.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Just as I write that, Ollie Robinson strikes! England do get an early breakthrough. Commentator's curse? Maybe. This is a lovely delivery. Perfect line and length. It is just ahead of a good length ball which means it draws the batter forward. Lands and moves away. It takes the outside edge of Warner's bat as he looks to defend and goes into the hands of Crawley at third slip. Ollie Robinson is delighted. Warner walks back for a duck. Warner actually put in a small stride forward. He ended up poking at the delivery. He was more worried about the back of a length ball and hence, did not put in a big stride which cost him his wicket. This was quite similar to the way Wood set him up in the previous game.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Broad bowls this down the leg side. Usman KhawajaÂ looks to clip it but it is way down the leg side.
Broad gets his line right this time and lands this on a length, outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ leaves it alone.
This is fuller and Usman KhawajaÂ goes for a drive. He gets a thick outside edge and the ball goes past gully for a couple.
Another full delivery, this time on middle. Usman KhawajaÂ drives this past mid on and gets another couple of runs. Broad is looking for some swing out there.
A fuller delivery again but this time down the leg side. Usman KhawajaÂ looks to flick it but misses.
Broad pulls his length back a little this time. He lands it on a length, on off. Usman KhawajaÂ is right behind it to block it.

That was close! A good leave in the end! Outside off, tails back in. Marnus Labuschagne covers his off pole and lets it be. It goes just past the off pole. Do not think he expected it to come back that much.

This is even better! Outstanding stuff. Ollie Robinson has his tail up here! Gets it to go the other way. Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Marnus Labuschagne comes forward to block but is beaten.
Solid! This will make Labuschagne feel good! On a length and on middle, this is pushed to mid on.

EDGED AND PUT DOWN! Crawley puts down what was not his catch. A life for the number 1 Test batter in the world. Another lovely nut from Ollie Robinson. This is on a length and around off, it lands and then moves away. Labuschagne plays the original trajectory but the ball takes the outside edge. It goes between first slip and second who are standing a little too close. It is actually Root's catch as it seems to be going straight to him. Crawley dives to his left but does not hang on. This can prove costly.
Is that an edge? No, it is bat hitting pad! On off, this lands and then shapes away again. Labuschagne looks to block. There is a noise as the ball passes the bat. Half an appeal but turned down.
A leave to end a superb over by Ollie Robinson! Quality stuff from the pacer, should have had a wicket. Outside off, Marnus lets it be.
Broad now goes fuller, gets this one to hold its line. Khawaja looks to drive but it goes off the outer half to point.

This is relentless stuff from the two opening bowlers. Just attacking the stumps on almost every delivery, testing the batter continously. Length and on middle, this lands and then moves away. Khawaja hangs back and tries to put bat on ball. This time it straightens and hits high on the pad.
Just outside off, Khawaja lets it be.
Yet another delivery, just outside off, Khawaja shoulders arms to this one.
That goes into the fence but dead ball signaled. On the pads, Khawaja leaves it alone. It hits the pad and goes down to the fine leg fence. Dead ball signaled as no shot was offered.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Khawaja now goes and England have both the openers back in the hut very cheaply. Two centuries in the last game but falls for a single digit score here. Broad also has one now. Hard hands once again. This is on a length and around off, it lands and moves away. Khawaja pushes at it with hard hands, he plays it well ahead of his body. Not what you want to do in seaming conditions. It goes off the outside edge and it is taken by Root at first slip. Australia in trouble here. England could have easily had three but this is a superb start for them.
Howout: c Joe Root b Stuart Broad

Commentary: FOUR! First boundary and Marnus LabuschagneÂ is off the mark! TooÂ straight from Ollie Robinson, on the pads, this is flicked through mid-wicket and it races away to the fence.
A length ball, around off, it lands and jags back in sharply. Marnus LabuschagneÂ leaves but this comes back in and hits him high on the pads.
Angles it on the pads, Marnus LabuschagneÂ plays it late and tucks it through square leg for a single.
Length and on off. Steven SmithÂ comes right across and misses his flick. It takes the thigh guard and goes to square leg.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN!Â What a start for England! Crawley takes the catch, he put one down before but holds onto this one. Smith walks back for a duck! This is slightly shorter than a length, around off. Again Steven SmithÂ shuffles way across and tries to block it but this moves away a bit and takes the outside edge. It goes to Zak CrawleyÂ at second slip who takes a low catch. Perfect start for England. Yet another low score for Steven Smith.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Length and on the pads, this is flicked to square leg.
Length ball, outside off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ shoulders arms to it.
This one angles in from outside off, fuller. Marnus LabuschagneÂ lets it through.
WIDE! A sharp bouncer from Broad, steep bounce as well. Marnus LabuschagneÂ sits under it. Good carry for the keeper as well.
BEATEN! Touch fuller, outside off, it straightens off the deck. Marnus LabuschagneÂ defends inside the line of the ball and gets beaten.
Length ball, outside off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ covers his stumps and leaves it alone.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Good shot! This will release some pressure! A rare loosenerÂ from Broad. Pitches it up, on off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length and on off. Head tucks it off the back foot through square leg for three runs. He is off the mark.
BEATEN AGAIN! Lovely bowling from Ollie RobinsonÂ so far! Keeping it tight by serving it in the channel! This is on a length, outside off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ looks to defend but misses.
FOUR! UppishÂ but safe! Full again, around off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ drives it uppishly and wide of the diving cover fielder for a boundary.
Good leave! This one comes back in, Short of a length, outside off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ covers his off stump and lets it through.
On a length, on middle. Blocked out.
A length ball, angling on the pads. Marnus LabuschagneÂ looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. Half-hearted appeal but this was going down.
Full ball, outside off, this is pushed on the off side.
Goes wide of the crease and slants it on a length, on middle. Head blocks it out.
On a length, around off. Head looks to cut but this is too close to the body. It goes off the under edge, past the off stump and to square leg. One.
Outside off, on a length. Left alone by Marnus.
FOUR! Anything overpitched and Marnus LabuschagneÂ is putting it away! Full and on middle. This is whipped through square leg for a boundary.
Length ball, way outside off. Easy leave for Labuschagne.
Length ball, angling across outside off. Head shoulders arms to it.
On the pads, this is tucked to square leg for a single.
Fuller, outside off. Left alone.
That whizzed pastÂ the leg stump! Length ball, angling down the leg side. Marnus LabuschagneÂ steps across and looks to flick but misses.
Again down the leg side. Labuschagne misses his flick.
This one comes back in very late, outside off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ shoulders arms to it.
Full ball, outside off. Head drives it to mid off. The fielder there half-stops and a single is taken.
Full again, on off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ looks to defend but gets an outside edge to gully. Got hurried up there.
Length and on the pads. Marnus LabuschagneÂ shuffles and nudges it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! Touch fuller, around off. Head leans and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Angles it on the pads. Head hops and wrists it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Width on offer! Good over for Australia, 11 coming off it! Short of a length, outside off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ gets on his toes and slaps it through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Woakes is greeted with a boundary! A fulller delivery outside off. Head leans forward and drives it through cover-point for a boundary.

In the air...but safe! Woakes pulls his length back this time and bowls this around off. Head looks to pull but completely miscues it. The ball goes high in the air and falls in a vacant area towards mid off. A single taken.
A good-length delivery outside off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ leaves it alone.

This time anÂ edge but soft hand there from Marnus Labuschagne. A good-length delivery around off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ presses forward to defend but gets a thick edge and just short of the third slip fielder.
FOUR! Runs are flowing now! A fuller delivery on middle. Marnus LabuschagneÂ leans forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for another boundary. 50 up for AustraliaÂ now.
A good-length delivery outside off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ covers his off pole and leaves it.
A length ball, outside off. Head lets it go comfortably.
Nice timing again by Head! Back of a length, outside off. Head rides the bounce and punches it through covers. Pope runs behind it and saves a run for his team. Three runs taken.
FOUR! Short ball and punished by Marnus Labuschagne! Wood bowls this short on off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ pulls this uppishly towards deep square leg and gets another boundary.

Another nice shot but Ben StokesÂ saves a boundaryÂ with a slide near the fence! A fuller delivery on middle. Marnus LabuschagneÂ drives it past mid on and the ball almost races away for a boundary before Stokes cuts it off. Three runs taken.
A length ball, on off. Head pushes it to covers with soft hands and gets a single.
FOUR! Another cracking shot! Wood has been poor to say the least today! Back of a length, outside off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ stands tall and punches it through covers for a boundary. Superb batting.
Woakes bowls this on a length, outside off. Head looks to cut it but the ball seams away and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Shorter length on middle this time. Head pulls it to deep mid-wicket and the batters run three again. This is poor bowling and great running by the batters.
Back of a length and down the leg side this time. Marnus LabuschagneÂ looks to clip it but misses.
On a length, on off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ blocks it off solidy this time.
This is better from Chris Woakes! A good-length delivery around off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ looks to defend but the ball seams away and hits him on the back leg.
A length ball, on off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ blocks it back to the bowler. Chris WoakesÂ stops it and is looking visibly frustrated.
Broad drifts it on the leg stump. Head works it through mid-wicket for a couple.
A length delivery outside off. Head lets it go this time.

A bit fuller delivery on off. Head is back on the delivery he should have been forward and ends up getting an inside edge onto his pads. The batters run a quick single as the ball rolls towards the on side. Good running.
A good-length delivery around off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ covers his off pole and lets it go.
A length delivery outside off and nipping in sharply. Marnus LabuschagneÂ shoulders his arms again.
Another length delivery outside off and another leave from Marnus Labuschagne. Broad bowls this on a length and tad wider outside off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ is happy to let it go.
On the fuller side and on off, Head strokes it back to the bowler. The swing and movement seems to have gone now.
Does get this one to shape back in a touch from outside off, not enough though to make the batter play.
Fuller this time and on off, Head goes hard at it, mistimes it towards mid off for one.

FOUR! What a shot by Marnus Labuschagne! A shot of authority and a player who is high on confidence right now. He walks right across and then whips this delivery on off over mid-wicket for a boundary. Absolutely no respect shown for Woakes there. Marnus Labuschagne into the 40s now.
Fuller and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne works it through square leg for one.
Just outside off, Head covers his off pole and lets it go.
And again, walks right across, this time the length is shorter and hence, he works it all along the ground through mid-wicket for two. Marnus Labuschagne is in the mood here.

Broad did not like that at all! Marnus Labuschagne comes down the track, he looks to hit it through the off side but gets an underedge back to the bowler. Broad has a shy at the keeper's end but hits ML by mistake. It was more of a message from Broad that stay back.
Solid now! This time Marnus Labuschagne holds his ground and plays this length ball to point.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
Well played! Good length and on off, Labuschagne stays back and blocks.
A really good over from Broad! Bowled with a lot of fire. The last ball though is a harmless one, outside off, easy leave.
Good length and on off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! That squirts off the outer half! Fuller and on off, shapes away late. Head looks to drive, this goes off the outside edge past point and into the boundary.
Good length again and on off, Head plays it late and on the off side.
Yet again attacks the stumps and on off, Head blocks.
Slightly shorter and on off, Head looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

OUT! TIMBER! What just happened there! That looked ugly! Marnus Labuschagne has been cleaned up around his legs but that dismissal just seemed ugly. Just like always, he shuffles across, gets over to the off pole. Broad goes full and straight on middle, Marnus Labuschagne gets into a tangle as he tries to clip it on the leg side. In the end, loses his balance, falls onto the ground. Misses the ball by a long way and the ball shatters the stumps behind. Broad is elated and Marnus Labuschagne is not sure about what just happened. It was a really good innings till it lasted but Australia needed him to go on. Replays actually shows he just planted his front foot way too across and hence, lost balance. Very unusual from Marnus Labuschagne. Really not sure what he just did there. England now back on top.
Howout: b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Full ball, outside off, Green pushes it to covers.
Length ball, outside off. Green leaves this wayward delivery.
Length again, outside off. Green shoulders arms to it.
Full ball, almost a yorker, on off. Green gets his bat down in time and blocks it.
Green is off the mark! A length ball, on the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single. Excellent over for England, they are on back on top at the verge of Dinner.
On middle, on a length. Blocked on the leg side.
Touch fuller, straight on middle. Green defends it off the front foot.
Angles a length ball, on middle, tucked away to square leg for one more.
Length ball, angling outside off, late swing there as well. Head leaves it alone.
On middle. Blocked out.
Another solid block from Travis Head. This was on a length and on off. That will be DinnerÂ on Day 1.
Wood starts with a good-length delivery outside off. Green leaves it alone comfortably. He would like to get little closer to the stumps.
A length ball, on off. Green drives it to cover-point and gets a single. First runÂ after Dinner.
Ouch! This hits Head on his helmet! A nasty pacy short ball on middle. Head is surprised by the bounce and pace and takes his eyes off the ball. He gets hit on the helmet but not much damage done.
Back of a length, on off. Head hops and blocks it onto the turf.
Another slightly shorter length delivery on off. Head defends this off the back foot.
Wood goes a tad fuller this time on middle. Head drives it past mid on and gets a couple. Good start from Wood to this second session.
A gentle loosener from Ollie Robinson. He lands it on a length, outside off. Green leaves it alone.
FOUR! Good shot! slightly fuller on off. Green plants his front foot forward and drives it left of mid off for a boundary. Nice timing there.
Pulls his length back a little on middle. Green works it to backward square leg for a single.
FOUR! Head is in no mood to play cautiously here! A fuller delivery on leg. Another medium pace delivery. Head whips this off his legs towards deep square leg for a boundary.
A length ball, on off. Head blocks it out this time towards the off side.
A good-length delivery outside off. Head leaves it alone.
Wood is bowling with good steam here. He lands it on a length, outside off. Gree leaves it alone as he covers his off pole.
Slightly fuller outside off by Wood. Green plants his front foot forward and then decides to let it go.
Play and a miss this time! A shorter length delivery outside off. Wood gets some extra bounce and Green misses his cut shot.
Angled into middle and leg this time. Green works it to mid-wicket for a single.
A slightly fuller delivery outside off. Head plays it from his crease towards covers and gets a single. He did well to get a bat on it.
100 up for Australia! A length ball, on off. Green gets across and works it to mid-wicket for another single.
Woakes starts with bowling in that channel around off. Green lets it go.
Woakes hits the length hard this time on off. Green is solid in his defence.
He goes fuller now. Green drives this off the front foot to covers. This is a better length from Woakes.
Pulls his length back a little and bowls this around off. Green leaves it alone.
Runs for Australia. A length ball, around off. Green plays it late and opens the face of his blade. He gets it through backward point for a couple.
Woakes goes fuller on off. Green drives it firmly back to the bowler.
Another shorter length delivery angled into the body of Travis Head. He plays it awkwardly towards the on side for a single. This is a better length against Head.
Wood goes short again on off. Green is upto the task and ducks under it.
Back of a length on off at 142 clicks. Green rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
Good running there. Back of a length, on off. Green pushes it off the back foot to covers and takes a quick single.
Wood goes fuller and Head drives it past mid off. Stokes runs behind it and cuts it off before the batters run three.

FOUR! Good bowling but is played well by Green! Back of a length, around off. Green stays back and pushes at it with soft hands. The ball catches the outside edge of his blade a little and runs through the gully region for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Head looks to cut it but misses. He is not shying away from playing his shots.
FOUR! Another superb shot from Head! Back of a length, around off. Head rides the bounce and punches it through point for a boundary. He is in great touch out here.
Good comeback! The last one was bowled a touch wide. This time he lands it on off and gets it to shape away. Head is beaten as he tries to block.
On the fuller side and on middle, Head strokes it back to the bowler.
A little too straight, comes back in. Head looks to flick but misses to get hit above the knee roll.
This one takes off! On a length and on off, extra bounce. Head does well to play it by taking a hand off the handle. A good over by Woakes, except for that boundary ball, he was on the money.
Angled into the pads, Green works it through mid-wicket for one.
On the pads, Head flicks it down to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Angled into the pads, Green works it through square leg for one.
Back of a length and on off, Head hops and guides it to point.
Looks to bowl a yorker but ends up bowling a low full toss, it is pushed to mid off for one.
A dot to end! Fuller and on middle, this is worked to mid on.

FOUR! Fifty for Head! Back in the side and back amongst the runs. Another important knock. Came out in tough conditions, his side was in trouble, weathered the storm early and is now cashing in. A big score is on the offer here. He gets a gift to get to the milestone. On the pads, this is worked down to the fine leg fence.
Back of a length and on off, Head pushes it to covers.
FOUR! Hammered! That is put away with disdain! Fuller and on off, Head throws the kitchen sink at it, he smashes it wide of mid off and into the fence.
Wood changes the angle, goes around the wicket and bowls it full and on off, this is driven to covers.
On the off pole, drags his length back too. Kept out.
Well fielded! Shorter in length and outside off, Head cuts, it goes towards point. The fielder there dives to his right and stops it well.
A fuller delivery on off. Green drives it to covers and gets a single.
Ohh..alomost drags it on! A fuller deliver on off. Head looks to drive but gets the inside edge onto his pads and ball rolls just away from the stumps.
A fuller delivery on off. Head drives it to long off for a single.
Slower in the air on off. Green defends this off the front foot.
Easy single there. A fuller delivery on off. Green pushes it to long on and gets a single.
Darted on middle and leg. Head works it to deep mid-wicket for a single. He uses his wrists to a good effect.
Full delivery around leg. Head flicks it to deep square leg for a single. An easy single given again. Poor cricket from England.
A length ball, on off. Green is solid in his front foot defence.
Overpitched on off. Green works it through mid-wicket with his wrists. The fielder there runs behind it and saves a run for his team with a dive near the fence. Three runs taken.
A length ball, on off. Head defends it off the outer half of his blade to point. He gets a single.
A length ball, on off with perfect seam position. Green is solid in his defence again.
Another length delivery on off. Green defends it comfortably yet again. Woakes is not getting much movement out there.
On off, this is pushed down to long off for one.
Flatter and on off, Green looks to drop and on the off side but Head sends him back.
Fuller and on the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on middle, Head works it to mid on.
On off, blocked.
This is quicker and on middle, skids through. Head gets his bat down in time and pushes it to covers.
Fuller and on off, Green strokes it wide of mid off for one.
On off, Head gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Length again and on off, this one jags back in. It is pushed to mid off.
Another back of a length ball, Head stays back and defends.
Keeps it behind a length and on off, Head pushes it to mid off.
On off, Head plays it late and on the off side, he wants a run but is sent back.
On off, Green defends.
On off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On the pads, Head looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
On middle, Green pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, kept out.
Angled into the pads, Green works it through square leg. The man at deep mid-wicket, runs to his right, dives and keeps it down to three.
On middle, Green works it through mid-wicket for one.
Goes fuller and around off, Head pushes it wide of mid off for one more. The two look at ease for now. Runs are also ciming quite easily.
And another single! On the pads, Green nudges it on the leg side. There is no pressure from England at the moment. They are unable to build any kind of pressure we should say.

FOUR! Not sure if the wicket has eased off or the batting is just too good at the moment! This is a back of a length delivery on off, Head goes back and pushes it through covers. This one races away to the fence.
Timed well again but finds mid off. Fuller and on off, it is hit right off the middle but to the fielder at mid off.
Another productive over for Australia! The last ball is played late and towards point for one.
Flatter and on middle, Head pushes it back to the bowler.
Slightly shorter in length, Head pushes it to covers.
Runs continue to come! Head comes down the track and also makes room. He hits it through covers for two.
Angled into the pads, Head works it through mid-wicket for one.
Two more! Slightly fuller and on off, Green pushes it through covers for two.
Fires it on off, Green stays back and defends.

FOUR! Edge but boundary for Head! Back of a length, aroundÂ off. Head is cramped for room but still goes for a back foot punch. He gets a thick outside edge and ball flies through the vacant slip corridor for a boundary. Just one slip in place.
Back of a length and down the leg side this time. Head looks to clip it but misses.
Back of a length again, around off. Head pushes it to third man for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Green plays away from his body and gets a thick outside edge. Te ball goes through backward point region and the batters run three before the fielder cuts it off.
Back of a length, on middle. Head works it to deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Head picks the length quickly again. This is back of a length, on off. Head rides the bounce and punches it through covers for a couple.
Broad starts with a full delivery outside off. Green is nicely forward to that one and drives it to covers. The fielder there stops it.
On a length, on middle. Green works it to backward square leg for a single.

FOUR! What a shot! He is looking in supreme touch here! Back of a length, around off. Head stays back and cuts it through point for a boundary, He is poicking the length so quickly that nothing is working against him.
Slightly fuller on off. Head drives it wide of mid off for a single.
FOUR! Glorious shot! An overpitched delivery on off. Green plants his front foot forward and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Green defends it off the back foot solidly.
Fuller on middle. Head skips down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
THREE BYES! A flatter delivery down the leg side. Head looks to clip it away but misses. Sam BillingsÂ fails to collect it cleanly too and the batters run three byes towards long leg.
A fuller delivery on middle. Green works it to mid-wicket.
100 runs partnership comes up! A fuller delivery that is turning back in. Green works it to square leg for a single. Superb partnership between these two.
Pushed through quicker outside off. Head looks to cut it but misses.
Slower in the air on middle. Head works it wide of mid on for a single.
Length and angling on off. Blocked out.
FOUR!Â Timing! A full ball, outside off. Head caresses it through covers and it races away to the fence. Some glorious drives from Travis HeadÂ in this innings.
Full and on off, driven nicely but straight to covers.
This one comes with the angle, on a length, outside off. Head looks to cut it but gets cramped for the room lately.
Slower ball, on off, tucked away to mid-wicket.
Length and on middle. Blocked out.
Tossed up, turning in, on middle, flicked to square leg.
Fuller and on middle. Blocked on the leg side.
Slightly short on off. Green gets on the back foot to defend it.
On middle, Green comes down the track to keep it out.
Flatter and on leg. Green pushes it off the inner half to the leg side.
Shorter and on middle. Green blocks it off the back foot. Not much turn to offer for Joe Root.
Length and on middle. Head stays back and blocks it out.
Length and on off. Head punches it to sweeper cover for a single. He moves into the 90s.
Length ball, way outside off. Green leaves it alone.
This is again outside off stump. Green covers his off stump and lets it through.
Much better! Fuller and on off, pushed to mid off.
This is on a length, outside off, slower ball as well. Green is touch early as he looks to push, he hits it towards covers.
Tossed up, on off, this is pushed through covers for a single.
Quick single! This is good running! Full ball, on off. Green pushes it to mid off and calls for a quick single, Makes it to the other end on time.
Flatter and on off. Kept out.
Darted on the pads, this is hit through square leg for a single.
On middle, this is short. Green rocks back and blocks it out.
Another short ball, on middle. Green defends this off the back foot.
FOUR! Travis HeadÂ moves to 96! A length ball, angling on the pads. Head whips it aerially over square leg for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Head hits it to deep point for one more.
Fuller ball, outside off. Green pushes it to covers.
BEATEN! Hint of away swing, on a length and outside off. Green has a poke at it but misses.
Outside off, fuller delivery, Green pushes it to covers.
On a length, on middle. Green defends it off the front foot.
Flatter on middle and angling in from 'round the wicket. Head works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Darted on the pads. Green works it to mid-wicket and another easy single taken.
Root fires this on quicker on middle. Head pushes it to mid on.
Angled into middle again. Head works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Quicker and flatter on off. Green easily knocks it to long on for a single.
Dot ball! He will have to wait for his century! A fuller delivery on off. Head drives it to the cover fielder.
Woakes bowls this fuller on off. Green drives it to mid off and gets a quick single. Here we go, Head on 99. Can he get a hundred off the next ball?
The wait continues! A fuller delivery on middle. Head calmly defends this back to the bowler.
Heart in the mouth moment! A leading edge but safe! A fuller delivery on middle. Head looks to work it away towards the on side but gets a leading edge towards mid on. Luckily for him it falls short.

100 for Travis Head! What a knock, a knock he will probably never forget! Absolutely stunning. Walked out when his team was 3 down for hardly anything and has single-handedly taken his side to safer shores on a wicket which can be considered as a really tough wicket to bat on. His second ton in this year's Ashes but this one is surely better than the last one. An innings full of class and some brilliant stroke making. He gets there in an edgy manner but he really won't care. It is a short ball outside off, Head looks to cut but this goes off the underedge down towards third man. The batters take two. The people in the ground are on their feet applauding the effort. He takes the helmet off and soaks it in. He has a chance to make it a big ton now.

OUT! TAKEN! Oh...Head departs on the very next ball after getting to the century! A fuller delivery on middle. Head looks to work it away towards the on side but gets the leading edge again. This time the ball travels towards mid on and Ollie RobinsonÂ there takes a good catch. So Head departs and this dangerous partnership is finally broken. Â Head walks back after another brilliant knock. His team was under the pump when he walked out to the middle and has managed to take his team to a much better position with his counter-attacking century. Can England capitalize on this breakthrough? They need a couple of quick wickets to get back into this game.
Howout: c Ollie Robinson b Chris Woakes

Commentary: AÂ  length delivery on off. Carey blocks it out solidly.
AÂ  flatter ball, on off. Green blocks it out.
Slightly shorter outside off. Green goes deep in his crease and pushes it to backward point for a couple.

Fifty for Green! A very calm and measured innings! Some really beautiful strokes so far in this knock. He was short of runs but Australia will hope this is the start of something. His third Test fifty. He has gone along things really nicely. A ton is on the offer here. He gets there by pushing it towards cover and getting to the other end.
Pushed quicker on off. Carey defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
Fuller delivery outside off. Carey drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
FOUR! Classy shot! Root serves this fuller outside off. Green leans forward and drives it crisply through covers for a boundary. Superb shot!
A length ball, on off. Carey blocks this solidly off the front foot.
Fuller this time on middle. Carey works it towards mid-wicket.
Pulls his length back and bowls this around off, Carey watches it till the end and lets it go.
Back of a length, around off again. Carey decides to leave it alone.
Woakes hit the length hard again and lands this on off. Carey defends this solidly off the front foot.
Nice stroke but straight to the fielder. Slightly fuller on off. Carey leans forward and drives it straight to mid off.
Slightly shorter and turning into middle and leg. Green works it to square leg.
A flatter delivery on middle. Green blocks it solidly.
Another flatter delivery on off. Green stays deep in his crease and blocks it.
Drifts down the leg side this time Root. Green clips it fine towards long leg for three runs. Good running.
AÂ  fuller delivery on middle. carely solidly blocks it.

Ohh...a scare for Carey on the last ball of the session! A flatter and quicker delivery angled into middle from 'round the wicket. Carey looks to push this towards the off side off the back foot. He gets an inside edge onto his pads and the ball rolls just awayÂ fromÂ stumps towards short fine leg. AustraliaÂ are 215/5 at Tea on Day 1.
Starts off with one from wide of the crease and angles it into middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Length and outside off now, left alone well.
First run of the session! Fuller and on middle, Green strokes it wide of mid on and gets to the other end.
Solid! On a good length and on off, Carey keeps it out.
Another one on a length and around off, Carey plays it right under his eyes.
On middle, Carey plays it back to the bowler.
Wood begins well! He has been expensive so far but needs to do well now. He lands it on a length and around off, defended.
Yet again on middle, Green plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Errs in line and pays the price! This is full and on middle, Green walks across and clips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Corrects his line and bowls it on a length and around off, defended.

FOUR! That was class personified! Wow! Beautiful! Shorter and on off, Green stands tall, gets on top of the bounce and pushes it past the cover region for a boundary. Second boundary in the over, Wood continues to leak runs.
Just not been at his best! Now slips one down the leg side, Green misses the flick.
On middle, Carey plays it back to the bowler.
On the stumps, Carey leans forward and keeps it out.
Two more! On the pads, this is clipped through square leg for two.
Good length and on off, Carey defends.
Length and outside off, Carey does not fiddle with it.
Another length delivery to end, it is outside off, Carey shoulders arms to this one.
On middle, Green stays back and blocks.
Cuts Green into half! Shorter and outside off, this lands and comes back in. Green looks to defend but it goes in between bat and body and to the keeper. It just about got to the keeper.
FOUR! Another lovely stroke! Classy! Shorter and on off, once again Green stands tall and gets on top of the bounce. He guides it through point for a boundary.
A short one and on the body, Green ducks under it.
A short one and on the body, Green evades it well.
A dot to end! On off, this is pushed to covers.
On a length, on off. Carey looks t play it late but gets an inside edge past the stumps and to the leg side. Single.
Length ball, outside off. Green leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Green taps it to covers.
Touch fuller, on middle. Green stays back and defends it to the leg side.
FOUR! Pierces through the gap! A full ball, outside off. Green drives it, beats the diving fielder and it races away to the fence.
Full ball, on off, driven nicely but finds cover.
Serves a short ball, just outside off. Carey arcs back and sways away from the line. Good bumper.
Angles it from around the wicket on the pads, this is flicked to square leg for one.
Lovely bowling! Targets the body with yet another bumper. Green stands tall and blocks it out.
Short but slanting down the leg side. Green evades it.
On a length, on middle. Green tucks it to short square leg. Aggressive bowling from Mark Wood.

OUT! TAKEN!Â Wood gets the wicket, he was not giving any freebie in this over. He was bowling with fire and pace. Excellent execution also, changes and comes in around the wicket. serves a short ball, on middle. Cameron GreenÂ looks to pull but it takes the top edge towards deep mid-wicket where Zak CrawleyÂ takes a good catch.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Mark Wood

Commentary: On a length, on the hips, tucked away to square leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Blocked out by Starc.
Full and slanting outside off. Left alone.
Full ball, just outside off. Starc shoulders arms to it.
Outside off again, Left alone.
Slower ball but continues to serve it outside off. Easy leave for Starc.
FOUR! Good shot! A short ball, outside off. Carey hops and slashes it over point for a boundary. Good reflexes from theÂ umpire as he sits under it quickly.
Short ball, on middle. Carey ducks under it. Some sawdust spread to the bowler's landing area.
Another bouncer from Wood, Carey lets it through.
Wood starts with a yorker, around the off pole. Carey gets his bat down in time to dig it out.

Top delivery! Wood serves a good-length delivery, around off and curling away late. Carey stays back to block but the ball zips past his outside edge. Wood appeals for a caught behind but the umpire says no. English skipper, Joe RootÂ has a word with his mates regarding review but they decide to go against it.
On a length, around off. Carey blocks it out solidly. Good start from Wood!
Broad starts with a wayward ball, down leg. Starc misses his flick and the ball goes through to the keeper.

Length ball, around off. Starc pushes it towards mid off and scampers through to the other end. The fielder at mid off scores a direct hit at the bowler's end but Starc was well home. First runs on Day 2 for the Aussies.
On a length, around off. Alex CareyÂ keeps it out watchfully.
A bit fuller in length, just outside off. Carey gets forward and drives it towards mid off.
On a length, just outside off and angling across the batter. Carey prods but shoulders his arms to this one.
Fuller-length ball, around off. Carey presses forward and pushes it to mid off.
Wood comes over the wicket this time to Starc and serves a full ball, around leg. Starc clips it off his pads towards the on side and gives the strike back to Carey.
Banged into the deck, around middle. Alex CareyÂ ducks underneath.
Back of a length, outside off. Alex CareyÂ keeps his bat inside the line of the ball and lets it through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, drifting onto the pad. Alex CareyÂ glances it towards fine leg and collects a run.
Short of a length, around off. Mitchell StarcÂ gets on top of the ball and blocks it with soft hands towards backward point.
Another ball, around the rib-cage. Starc stays back and tucks it towards mid-wicket. Just 2 runs off the over!
Length ball, around leg. Alex CareyÂ flicks it towards square leg and takes off for a quick run.
Good-length ball, just outside off and shaping away late. Mitchell StarcÂ leaves it alone.
A bit fuller this time, well outside off. Mitchell StarcÂ lets it through to the keeper.
Broad comes 'round the wicket now and hurls a fuller-length delivery, around off. Starc prods and pushes it towards mid off.
Length ball, jagging back in from outside off. Mitchell StarcÂ presses forward and eases it back past the bowler towards mid on. Broad dives to stop the ball but the ball goes past him.
Fuller in length, outside off. Mitchell StarcÂ lunges forward and pushes it wide of mid off to collect a single.
Short of a length, around middle. Starc hangs back and blocks it out with ease.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mark WoodÂ strikes for EnglandÂ early on Day 2 and sends back Starc! Wood hurls a bumper, around middle. Starc looks to pull but the ball hurries onto him and it goes off the top edge, high in the air, just over the square leg fielder. Rory BurnsÂ at square leg backtracks and takes a good catch. Big wicket this for EnglandÂ as Starc could be very dangerous at this stage of the innings.
Howout: c Rory Burns b Mark Wood

Commentary: Banged into the deck, around middle. Pat CumminsÂ ducks underneath watchfully.
Good-length delivery, around off. Pat CumminsÂ blocks it out.
Another short ball, but this time it is way down leg. Pat CumminsÂ offers no shot to this one.
Wood comes 'round the wicket and hurls a bumper, around middle. Cummins looks to leave it but the ball goes on with the angle and hits him on his chest guard.
Good-length ball, around off. Alex CareyÂ defends it off the front foot.
Another good-length ball, on off. Carey is solid in his front foot defense.
Broad bowls a bouncer, around middle. Carey hangs back and pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg and gives the strike back to his skipper.
On a length, outside off. Pat CumminsÂ leaves it alone.
Leg bye! Length ball, nipping back in from off. Cummins misses his flick and gets hit on his pad. The ball rolls to the leg side and the batters sneak in a leg bye.
Short-of-a-length delivery, around middle. Carey stays back and punches it towards mid on.
Wood bangs it in from 'round the wicket. Around middle but Cummins hops back to block it.
Short again, on the body. Cummins awkwardly taps it past square leg for one. He was probably looking to duck at it at first but decided to play it in the end.
Wood persisting with the short stuff. Carey backs away this time so Wood follows him with a short one. Carey looks to cut it away but is beaten.
Back of a length, angling down the leg side. Carey leaves it alone.

Good bowling. Bumper, outside off. Carey looks to block but the ball balloons up and goes towards fine leg for one. That single brings up 250 for the Aussies. A good effort by them after losing 3 early wickets on this deck.
Cummins ducks under this one and lets the keeper collect it.
Nice and full, on off. Worked to mid-wicket.
Nearly a drag on! Full and wide outside off. Carey goes at it with his hands but gets the inside edge. Luckily, the ball hits his pads and rolls away.
Short, on off. Carey pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, around off. Cummins taps it towards cover.
Takes him this time. Short and down the leg side. Cummins pulls it to fine leg for one.
Over the wicket and Broad lands this on a length, around off. Carey looks to punch it away but gets it off the inner half back to the bowler.

OUT! TAKEN! The trap has worked and Wood has been rewarded with a wicket here!Â âPut the cheese in the trap, in goes the mouse, off goes his headâ the late great Bob Willis once said on air and this is exactly what happened. The ploy was simple. Have people back for the hook shot and have the relentless Mark Wood give the batters chin music. This is a short one, on middle. Cummins goes for the hook and hits it straight to deep square leg. Zak CrawleyÂ takes his third catch of the innings and Australia lose their skipper.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Mark Wood

Commentary: Back of a length, on off. Lyon pulls it away past mid-wicket for one.
A bumper, on off. Carey ducks under it.
Well played. Back of a length, around off. Carey sways away from the line of the ball and runs it to third man for one.

SIX! The ploy almost works again! Almost being the key word as Lyon gets a maximum here! A bumper, on the body. The off-spinner pulls it in the air. There are two men in the deep. The fielders from deep square leg and deep mid-wicket converge but neither of them makes a full-hearted effort to get to the ball. Woakes from deep mid-wicket almost gets there but the ball sails over the fence.
This goes way over Lyon's head as Wood digs it short.
Nice and full, on the pads. Worked towards deep mid-wicket. Broad runs in from the deep but fumbles while trying to pick the ball up. Two taken.
Clipped off the pads to deep square leg. This time Broad does the work neatly and gets a mild applause from the crowd.
On a length, on off. Lyon blocks it from the crease.
Nice and full, on middle. Lyon offers the full face of the bat and pushes it to mid on.
Length delivery, around off. Lyon gets a bit forward to block it.
Good-length delivery, on off. Lyon pushes it to mid off.
Carey hops up and taps it to point.
Bumper way down the leg side. Carey lets it go.

FOUR! Just wide! Carey decides to take it on this time! Short and just down the leg side. Carey goes for the pull but gets some glove on it. Billings throws himself to his right but cannot get there. Boundary.
Length, on off. Swiped away to deep square leg by Carey for one.

SIX! HO HO! Ricky Ponting would be proud of that shot! Lyon has hit that so very well. A bumper on the body and Lyon hooks it way over the square leg fence. The fielders in the deep are mere spectators.

SIX! Jeez! The GOAT has done it again! Short of a length, around off this time. Lyon pulls it way over the mid-wicket fence this time. He gives some catching practice to a few boys on the grass banks, but they drop it! 19 off 9 is Lyon.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Full, on off. Pushed to mid off by Carey.

OUT! BOWLED! Carey departs now! Well bowled by Woakes though. He bowls it on a length, right on the off pole. Carey leaves a bit of the gap between his bat and pads while looking to block it and that proves to be his undoing. The ball takes the inside edge and goes back onto hit the stumps.
Howout: b Chris Woakes

Commentary: On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, on middle. Boland blocks it from the crease.
Full and outside off. Boland looks to drive but gets the outer half of the bat towards point.
Full, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Very full again, on off. Lyon pushes it to mid off.
Length ball, on off. Lyon gets forward to block it.
Broad fires a yorker, just outside off. Lyon fails to block it. Lyon asks Broad how did that miss the stumps?
Full, on off. Pushed to mid off.
A low full toss, on the pads. Lyon helps it to fine leg for a couple.
Length, on off. Blocked out.
Too high this time with a bumper as Boland ducks under it. Wide called.
Beaten! On a length, just outside off. Boland sticks his bat out but it goes past the outside edge.
FOUR! Edged away! Length, around off. Boland gets the outside edge while looking to block. It runs past the diving third slip fielder for a boundary.
Well bowled and well played. Woakes slips a full one, on middle and Boland blocks it out.
FOUR! Oh, that is a top shot! Full, on the pads. Boland flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller and outside off. Boland gets the outside edge through the slip cordon for a couple this time.
Length, around off. Lyon gets the outside edge but it drops short of gully.
Fuller, on the pads. Flicked to the leg side.
On a length, on the pads. Lyon works it past square leg for one.
Length, on off. Blocked out.
A dot ball as Boland is solid in his defence.
Fuller and a bit wider outside off. Boland leaves it.
On a length, on off. Lyon pushes it towards cover.
Short this time, outside off. Lyon misses the pull.
FOUR! Oh, that is flayed away! Shorter and wider outside off. Lyon rocks back and cuts it past backward point for a boundary.

DROPPED! A great effort by Billings though! Back of a length, on off. Lyon goes for the slog but gets the top edge this time. The ball goes high in the air towards square leg. Billings gives it a chase and almost gets there too. He puts in a dive but it goes just past his fingertips. That brings up 300 for Australia.
Full, on off. Lyon works it wide of mid on for one.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Broad looks for the inswinging yorker, on off. Lyon digs it out.
A length ball, around middle. Lyon hangs deep and flicks it through square leg, albeit a bit awkwardly and picks up another couple of runs.
Just about keeps it out does Nathan Lyon. Fullish ball, tailing into middle and leg. Lyon does well to get a bat on it.

OUT! Cleaned up! Stuart BroadÂ knocks over Nathan LyonÂ and the Aussies are finally bundled out. Broad bowls a length ball, right on top of off and that's where you want to be as a pacer. Lyon backs away and looks to clobber it on the leg side but gets comprehensively beaten. The ball goes on to knock over the bails and Broad has his third wicket. AustraliaÂ finish with 303 runs on the board.
Howout: b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Back of a length, around off. Rory BurnsÂ stays back and blocks it out to the off side.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested! This isÂ a length ball, jagging back in late from off. Burns misses his flick and gets rapped on his pad. That would have certainly gone down leg.
Back of a length, around off. Rory BurnsÂ defends it off the back foot.
A fuller delivery this time, at 144 kph and outside off. Burns just watches it go past him.
Too close for comfort! A cross-seamer, around the top of off. Rory BurnsÂ goes back to defend and almost ends up chopping it back onto the stumps.

Beaten! Good length, just around the off pole and the ball zips past the outside edge as Burns looks to block. There was a huge noise though but no one went up. A maiden to start with from Mitchell Starc. UltraEdge shows that there was a huge nick but surprisingly no one heard it.
A length ball, outside off and nipping in. Crawley leaves it alone.
England are away. Length again, on off and this is nudged through gully with soft hands for a couple.
Sliding down leg, Crawley misses the flick.

OUT! RUN OUT! Absolutely catastrophic for EnglandÂ and Rory Burns! On off, Zak CrawleyÂ presses forward and pushes it towards covers. He wants the single but his partner hesitates a bit. They do go for it in the end but just that split second of hesitation has cost England big time. Marnus LabuschagneÂ picks up the ball and hits the stumps at the batter's end. The third umpire is called in and the replay shows that Burns does not have any part of his bat inside the crease. Well, he doesn't getÂ off the hook twice.
Howout: run out (Marnus Labuschagne)

Commentary: Back of a length, over off. Malan defends it off the back foot but is a bit taken aback by the extra bounce.
Through the slips! A good-length ball, outside off. Malan has a poke at it and gets the outside edge but luckily for him, the ball goes past third slip and they get a single.
A length ball, outside off and Malan doesn't play at it.
Starc goes fuller and at the off stump. Malan punches it nicely towards mid off.
Length again, at 144 kph and sliding down the leg side. Malan looks to tuck it away but misses.
Malan is flirting with balls outside off and that could be dangerous. Slightly fuller, outside off and Malan looks for the cover drive. The ball zips past his outside edge.
FOUR! Nicely put away. A gentle loosener from Starc, fuller and on middle. Dawid MalanÂ works it nicely through mid-wicket and picks up a boundary.
Pacy bumper this time, around 142 kph and over off. Malan looks to uppercut it but gets undone by the extra bounce.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, around off and just holding its line. Crawley looks to block but gets beaten.

Peach! Very similar to the previous delivery but even better this time. On a good length, around off and this one just seams away after picthing. Crawley presses forward to block but gets beaten on the outside edge again.
A bit shorter, at the body. Crawley hops back and works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
On off and angling across the left-hander. Malan leaves it alone.

Close! A length ball, around leg. This one just nips back in a bit and Malan gets rapped on the pads. The hosts appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Probably a touch too high and maybe sliding down leg too.
Length again, on the pads. Malan looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pads. Maybe it missed the pads as Malan seems stinged by it.
FOUR! Starc isn't getting it right here. Sort of a half-volley, around off. Zak CrawleyÂ plays a lovely cover drive as he leans into the shot and gets a boundary as well.
FOUR LEG BYES! Shorter ball, around leg. Crawley looks to tuck it fine but the ball comes off the hips and does run away fine and into the fence.
Better from Mitchell Starc. On a good length, on off and pushed across the batter. Crawley lets it be.
On top of middle and defended towards mid on.

FOUR! Sweet timing again from Zak Crawley. Starc overpitches again as he looks for some swing, which isn't there at the moment. Crawley stands tall and punches it past mid off. Marnus LabuschagneÂ gives chase and puts in the dive but it goes in vain.
Back of a length, around leg. This is dabbed down towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length, going on with the angle from off. Dawid MalanÂ leaves it alone and the ball goes just over the off stump. Cummins has his hands on his head.
Play and a miss! Length ball, just outside off and shaping away a bit. Dawid MalanÂ looks for a booming drive through the cover region but the ball goes past his blade.
Fuller in length, on middle. Dawid MalanÂ flicks it towards Scott BolandÂ at mid on who fumbles and the ball goes past him. The batters collect a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Zak CrawleyÂ lets it through to the keeper.

FOUR! Uppish but it flies past the backward point fielder. Fuller in length, outside off. Zak CrawleyÂ looks to drive but it goes off the outside half of the bat past the backward point fielder for a boundary.
On a length, around off. Zak CrawleyÂ blocks it off the front foot.
Boland starts with a length ball, just outside off. Dawid MalanÂ shoulders his arms to it.
Good-length delivery, around off. Dawid MalanÂ blocks it to the off side.
BEATEN! Fuller in length, well outside off. Dawid MalanÂ gets sucked into the cover drive yet again and the ball goes past his outside edge.
Short of a length, around off. Dawid MalanÂ hangs back to block but it goes off the inside edge towards the leg side.
Back of a length, around off. Dawid MalanÂ blocks it out solidly.
Good-length delivery, around off. Dawid MalanÂ hops in his crease and defends it.
Fuller in length, just outside off. Zak CrawleyÂ presses forward and keeps it out.

Length ball, around middle. Zak CrawleyÂ flicks it past the mid on fielder. Mitchell StarcÂ at mid on gives it a chase and keeps the ball in play by sliding just in front of the ropes. The batters take three runs.
Back of a length, around off. Dawid MalanÂ taps it to the off side and takes off for a quick single.
This isÂ on a length, just outside off. Zak CrawleyÂ blocks it to the off side.
A stifled appeal for LBW but the umpire says no! Good-length ball, just outside off. Crawley offers no shot to this one and the ball brushes his pad before going to the keeper.

OUT! TAKEN! Pat Cummins strikes and gets the wicket of Zak Crawley! The ploy to keep a short leg fielderÂ in place has done wonders for the hosts and EnglandÂ lose their second wicket. Cummins serves a back-of-a-length ball, angling in from middle. Crawley looks to keep it out but it goes off the inside edge and the ball pops up straight towards Travis HeadÂ at short leg who takes a sitter. England's trouble with the bat continues!
Howout: c Travis Head b Pat Cummins

Commentary: On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, around off. Malan blocks it from the crease.
Fuller, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off and drawing Malan for the drive. The batter gets it off the inner half to the leg side.
Just a touch shorter, outside off. Malan taps it towards point.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
On a length, wide enough for Root to leave his first delivery.

Big appeal but big inside edge on it! Length, around off. It comes back in sharply as Root looks to block. He gets a big inside edge on the pads but there is a big appeal by all the fielders. Good decision to not review that as there was a big inside edge on that.
On a length, outside off. Blocked out.
Fuller, just outside off. Root taps it to cover.
OUCH! Length, lands on off and comes back in. Root looks to block but gets hit near the box yet again.
Play and a miss! Cummins hurls it fuller, outside off. This shapes away and goes past Root's attempted drive.Â Brilliant bowling by the Australian skipper to his counterpart.
Full, on off. Blocked out.
Malan takes a step down the track and taps it to cover.
Length ball, on off. Malan blocks it with soft hands.
A bit wider and fuller this time. Malan makes no attempt to play at it.
Boland comes 'round the wicket and bowls it full, outside off. Malan daps it towards gully but the fielder dives and stops it.
Length and down the leg side. Malan works it to fine leg for a single.
Length, on middle. This comes back in again. Root misses his defence and gets hit on the thigh. But it does deflect and hits him near the box again!
Nicely played. Fuller, outside off. Root comes down a bit and then works it past mid-wicket. Starc chases and slides to stop it. Three taken.
A bumper, outside off. Malan leaves it and Carey leaps to just about stop it.
Length, on off. Malan blocks it from the crease.
This stays a bit low! Length, sixth-stump channel so Malan lets Carey do some work before Dinner and collect it.
Bit more work for Carey again! Cummins bowls it down the leg side. Malan misses the glance and Carey dives down to his right to block it. That is Dinner on Day 2!
Boland is right on the money after the break. He bowls a length ball, on off. Root stays in the crease to block it.
Nice and full, on off. Root pushes it to mid on.
Fuller, around off. Root blocks it well.
A bit shorter and wider outside off. Root leaves it alone.
Length, on the pads. Root works it past square leg for a single.
Boland bowls it fuller, on off. Malan drives it nicely to mid off.
Length ball, down the leg side. Root lets Carey collect it.
Better. Length ball, just outside off. Root is forced to play at it and he blocks it.
Length ball, angling back in from off. Root works it past square leg for a couple.
A bit shorter and wider. Root pushes it to cover.
Green bowls it full, on off. Blocked out by Root.

Beaten! Ohhs and ahhs from the slip cordon as this one goes just past the outside edge! Green serves a length ball, in the corridor outside off. It shapes away just enough to go past Root's attempted defence.
Length, on off. Blocked out.
Lands fuller, outside off and comes back in with the angle. Malan shoulders his arms.
Full and outside off. Left alone.
Boland drags his length back a bit but keeps bowling it quite wide outside off. Malan prods forwards but leaves it yet again.
Boland goes on the pads now. Malan gets hit on the pads while looking to block.
Back of a length, just outside off. There is a bit of extra bounce on that and Malan takes his hand off the bat while looking to block. It goes towards point.
Runs for Root! Full, on off. He works it past mid-wicket. Two fielders chase it. Cummins slides and drags it back in. While the other one throws it back. Three runs.
FOUR! No stopping that one! Full, outside off. Malan drives it past covers for a boundary.

Noise as the ball goes past the bat! AustraliaÂ decide not to review it though. Oh boy, there is a spike as the ball goes past the bat on UltraEdgeÂ and Justin Langer cannot believe it! The ball is far away from the pad and even the bat hasn't brushed the pads!Â This lands on off, on a length. Malan looks to block but leaves a gap between his bat and pad. The ball goes through that gap and goes to the keeper. There is an appeal for caught behind but the umpire is not interested. Cummins has a word with his bowler but decides not to review this. Australia could have had their third! Cummins probably thought that it hit the pad and Carey wasn't too excited either. Green was the most excited but couldn't convince his skipper to take the review.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Malan steers it to gully.
Inside edge on the pads! Short of a length, outside off. Malan looks to punch it away but gets the inside edge back on the pads.
Good-length ball, outside off and shaping away nicely. Root hangs back and looks to push it through covers but gets beaten past the outside edge.
FOUR! Lovely timing from Joe Root. This is angled into the pads and Root just tucks it through square leg and finds the boundary.
Short of a good length, over middle. Root pushes it off the back foot towards mid-wicket for a quick single.
Boland is bowling a lovely length here. Around off, angling in and Malan looks to play it out with soft hands. He gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On off. Blocked out.
BEATEN! Another top delivery from Boland! Good-length delivery, outside off and jagging back in late. Malan stays back to block but he misses as the ball goes past his outside edge.
On a good length, around the off pole. Root goes on the back foot to tuck it away leg side but gets an inside edge past square leg and they get through for a single.
Length again, a bit wide of off stump and left alone by Malan.
Slightly fuller this time from Green and around off. Malan stands tall and strokes it towards cover-point. The fielder over there dives to his left to make a good stop.
Full again, trying to attack the pads but Malan eases it towards mid on.
FOUR! Green needs to be a bit more patient here. He offers width and Malan duly obliges. Shortish ball, outside off and this is slapped through point for a boundary.
On a good length, around off and cut away towards point.
In that channel around off and angling it in at around 137 kph. Joe RootÂ makes an assured leave.

FOUR! Just eased through the off side. Boland pitches it up and the ball shapes away. Root though leans in and drives it beautifully through covers for another boundary. The runs are flowing a bit here for England.
A length ball, wide of off stump. Left alone by Root.
This one nips back in from off stump. Root is caught on the crease a bit but does well to keep it out.
Back of a length, around off. Root hangs back and eases it on the off side for a single.
Angled in at off from 'round the wicket. Malan stays solid in defense.
A bit of yes and no but no damage done. Back of a length, around off. Root drops it on the off side and looks for the quick single but Malan sends him back and rightly so.
Green goes a bit fuller and keeps it close to the off pole. Root edges it down with soft hands towards gully.
Misfield from Marnus. A length ball, on off and Joe RootÂ punches it firmly towards covers. Marnus doesn't collect it cleanly and the batters get one.
Oi, that was closer than Malan thought. This one shapes in beautifully from outside off and Malan leaves it on line. The ball ends up going just past the off stump.
Assured leave this time from Dawid Malan. Good-length ball, around off and left alone.
FOUR! Gets it through does Malan and it's yet another boundary for the visitors. A touch shorter and outside off. Malan hangs back and just guides it past backward point for a boundary.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! Starc starts with a half-volley, outside off. Root lunges forward and caresses it through the cover region to fetch himself a boundary.
Length ball, around middle and leg. Joe RootÂ flicks it off his pads and collects a couple of runs.

NOT OUT! Joe RootÂ SURVIVES! This was a good-length ball, just outside off and shaping away a bit after landing. Root looks to drive it down the ground but he misses and gets hit on his pad. Starc puts in an appeal but the umpire says no. Cummins opts for a review but the Ball Tracker suggests that the impact is umpire's call and wickets missing.
Length ball, around leg. Joe RootÂ flicks it through the mid-wicket region. The fielder there gives it a chase and cuts it off. The batters take three runs.
On a length, on off. Dawid MalanÂ blocks it out.
FOUR! Nicely done! Fuller in length, outside off. Malan lunges forward and caresses it through the cover region. The ball races away to the fence.
Back of a length, around off. Joe RootÂ stays back and taps it towards backward point.
Top delivery from the skipper! This is a yorker-length ball, around off. Root looks to dig it out and gets an inside edge onto his pad. Had there been no bat involved, Root was a goner!
Good-length ball, around off. Root taps it to the off side and scampers through to the other end.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Oh, dear! A wicket against the run of play and Malan would not believe his luck here! He gets strangled down the leg side. This is a length ball, angling in from leg. Malan looks to flick but he only manages a tickle to the right of the keeper. Alex CareyÂ moves there and pouches it with ease. Huge blow this for EnglandÂ as these two were looking quite good in the middle.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Back of a length, around off. Ben StokesÂ gets behind the line of the ball to defend it.
Fuller in length this time, outside off. Ben StokesÂ leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.

A length ball, around leg. Joe RootÂ glances it wide of the fine leg fielder. Scott BolandÂ there moves across to his right and cuts it off just in front of the ropes. The batters collect a couple of runs. A huge round of applause for Boland as he stops the ball. He is someone who can do no wrong in the series and these scenes were seen in Sydney too. What a start for him in Test cricket!
Good-length ball, angling across the batter from outside off.Â Joe RootÂ stays back and offers no shot to this one.
Starc drags his length back a bit, around middle. Joe RootÂ gets back in his crease and tucks it wide of the mid-wicket fielder for a single.
Starc errs in line this time and sprays it down leg. Ben StokesÂ misses his flick and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, around middle. Ben StokesÂ nudges it towards square leg.

Swing and a miss! Length ball, well outside off. Ben StokesÂ throws his bat at it but fails to connect. There might have been a faint edge on that and there was a noise. But regardless, it didn't carry to the keeper.
Length ball, on off. Joe RootÂ drives it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, coming in with the angle from outside off. Joe RootÂ stays back to block but he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad.
Fuller in length, around middle. Joe RootÂ drives it towards mid on.

OUT! LBW! The Aussie skipper gets rid of the English skipper and EnglandÂ are in deep, deep trouble now! This isÂ a length ball, just outside off and nipping back in sharply. Root stays back, hops in his crease to flick it away but misses and gets rapped in front. Cummins appeals and the umpire raises his dreaded finger in no time. Root is not even bothered with a prolonged discussion as to whether he should take the review or not. He walks away simply after having a word with his partner.Â Huge moment in this Test match as England's most dependable batter, Joe Root walks back to the hut.
Howout: lbw b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Good-length ball, around middle and leg. Ollie PopeÂ tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Full ball, outside off. Ollie PopeÂ pushes it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, well outside off. Ben StokesÂ lets it sail through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ben StokesÂ shoulders his arms to this one.
On a length, around off. Ben StokesÂ gets behind the line of the ball to block it out.

FOUR! Jeez! That could have been the fifth one for the Aussies! This was a good-length ball, angling in from middle. Stokes looks to flick it but he gets a tickle on it and the ball goes past the diving leg slip fielder for a boundary.
Full-length ball, outside off. Ben StokesÂ squeezes it out towards mid on.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a top catch from the GOAT at backward point. EnglandÂ are falling like a pack of cards now and the Aussies are all over the tourists! This was a short-of-a-length delivery, just outside off. Stokes hangs back and cuts hard but finds Nathan LyonÂ at backward point who moves to his left quickly, gets low and takes a very good low catch. Stokes stands there in disbeleif and then makes his way back to the pavilion.
Howout: c Nathan Lyon b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Length ball, on off. Pope blocks but gets it off the inner half to mid-wicket.
Length, lands on middle and angles down the leg side. Pope looks to work it away but misses.
Length and on the pads. Pope gets it towards fine leg for a single.
'NO RUN!' yells Sam BillingsÂ as he blocks this length ball, on off. Must be a good feeling to hit your first ball in Tests from the middle of the bat.
Billings is off the mark! His first runs in Test cricket! Full, on the pads. He works it wide of deep backward square leg for a couple.
Nice and full, on off. Billings gets forward to block it.
Short of a length, down the leg side. Pope leaves it alone.
Full, on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Top shot! Overpitched and outside off. Pope nicely drives it past covers for a boundary.
FOUR! Brilliant again. Starc overcompensatesÂ and bowls it full, on the pads. Pope whips it past mid on for a boundary.
Oh beaten! This lands on the fourth stump and goes on with the angle. Pope is beaten as he looks to block.
And again! This is a bit closer to the off pole but angling away. Pope is glued to the crease while looking to block and it goes past the outside edge.
Beaten again! Now, Billings is facing the music! Length ball, just outside off. Billings looks to block but the ball holds its line and goes past the outside edge.
Jaffa! This is lovely bowling from Cummins! Billings is once again beaten while looking to block due to the hint of away shape. It has gotten a bitÂ overcast and that should help the pacers.
Fuller, on off. Tapped to gully.
FOUR! Oh, top shot! A bit overpitched and outside off. Billings drives it uppishly but past mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! And again! This is lovely bowling from Billings! Full again, around off. He drives it handsomely to the long off for one.
Length, on off. Tapped towards gully and a few Aussie fielders get a bit chirpy.
Full, just outside off. Blocked out.
Tap and run. Length ball, on off. Pope shuffles across and taps it to the leg side for a quick single.
Back of a length, on off. Tapped out. A solid defence and a 'no run!' from Billings.
Length ball, on the pads. Billings looks to flick it away but gets hit high on the pads.
Back of a length, on off. Billings blocks from back on the deck.
Oooh! Length and just outside off. Billings decides to leave it a bit too late. The ball hits the toe end and goes towards the slip cordon.
Short of a length, outside off. Pope leaves it at the last moment. The ball bounces on its way to the keeper.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Length, on middle. Pope shuffles a tiny bit and flicks it past mid on for a boundary.
What happened there? This lands on a length, wide outside off and comes back in very sharply. Pope leaves it alone but gets hit high on the pads.
A short one, down the leg side. Pope leaves it and Carey moves to hisÂ left to gather it.
On a length, on the pads. Worked to fine leg for a single.
Lands on a length, wide outside off and comes back in sharply. Billings gets hit on the body while looking to block.
Lovely away shape. Boland is always on song. A length ball, outside off and inviting the drive. Pope goes for it but gets well beaten.
The ball is moving a bit here. Around off and well left by Pope.
Length again, keeping it close to the off stump. Pope shoulders arms.
This is angled in on middle and Pope pushes it out towards mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Scott BolandÂ is just relentless and does get the breakthrough. Boland pitches it a bit further up and keeps the ball in the channel around off. Ollie PopeÂ is forced into pressing forward and he does so, looking to push it out wide. The ball shapes away after pitching and the outside edge is taken. Alex CareyÂ moves to his right and takes an easy catch.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Scott Boland

Commentary: Dropped! My word, David WarnerÂ has dropped a dolly. Boland almost had two in two and he really should have. Another lovely away-shaping delivery from Boland. Woakes is forced to play at it and gets the outside edge. The ball goes to Warner at first slip and it is at a comfortable height but he spills it.
Full, outside off. Billings gets the inside edge on the pads.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, on off. Blocked to mid on by Billings.
FOUR! That is nicely played by Billings! Short of a length, outside off. He gets on his toes and punches it past covers for a boundary.
Short of a length, on the body. Billings works it off the bottom edge, through square leg for a single.
Bumper, on off. Woakes sits under it.
Nice and full, but wide enough for Billings to leave it with ease.
A bit closer to the off pole and nice away shape on that. Left alone yet again.
Good-length ball, outside off and curling away late. Sam BillingsÂ has a tentative poke at it but the ball goes past his outside edge.
Beaten! That is the perfect delivery! Length ball, quite close to the off pole so Billings has to play at it. But the ball holds its line and goes past the outside edge.
Nice and full, around off. Sam gets forward to block.
On a length, on off. Pushed past point. Billings thinks of the single for a second but decides against it in the end.
Fuller, on off. Blocked out.
Beaten! Length ball, just outside off. Woakes looks to block it from the crease but it shapes away and goes past the bat.
FOUR! Well played. On a length, around off. Woakes plays it with soft hands past second slip for a boundary.
Short and down the leg side. Woakes leaves it alone.
Beaten! Full, just outside off. Woakes goes for the drive but is beaten.
Length ball, around off. Pushed away by Woakes.

Length and down the leg side. Billings gets hit on the pads while looking to flick. There is an appeal but only by two players. The first one is the bowler and the second one is the man at first slip. ThatÂ could be Marnus Labuschagne!
FOUR! Length ball, around off. Billings gets the outside edge towards third man again. It goes past the cordon and runs to the fence.
Full, lands outside off and comes back in. Billings is hit on the pads while looking to flick.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Length but wide enough for Billings to leave it with ease.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
Length ball, shapes away after landing outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, on off. Woakes hops up to block it.
Cameron GreenÂ goes agonizingly past the outside edge again! He pitches it up, just outside off. Woakes is glued to the crease as he looks to block but the ball zips past the bat.
Fuller, on middle. Woakes looks to work it away but gets the leading edge towards cover.
Banged in short, on middle. Woakes taps it towards square leg for one.
Length ball, around off. Billings gets the outside edge towards the slip cordon.

DROPPED! That is poor! Khawaja should have left Smith take it! Full and wide outside off. Woakes goes for the drive away from his body but gets the outside edge. Now, the ball flies to the slip cordon. Mark Waugh has been saying for a while now that the slips are too close together and that could be an issue. Now, Khawaja, who is at third slip, moves to his left side. Natural side for him so there's that. But he goes right in front of Smith, who is at second slip to take it. Smith could have easily taken that to his right with minimal movement but Khawaja goes for it and drops it!
Boland goes full and wide. Woakes doesn't play at it.
