Boland pulls his length back and bowls it around off. Woakes hops and gets behind the line of the ball to block it out.
Trying to nip it back in from wide outside off. The ball does come back a bit but Woakes leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, on off and solid block off the front foot by Woakes.
Woakes survives. Boland goes full and outside off, inviting the drive but Woakes times it sweetly towards cover. Tea is taken with England reeling at 124/6!
Green starts with a back-of-a-length delivery, around off. Billings gets right behind the line of the ball to block it.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, outside off and nipping away a bit. Billings looks to block but the ball goes past his blade.
Good-length ball, jagging back in sharply from outside off. Sam BillingsÂ stays back to defend but he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad. A stifled appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head.
Full ball, outside off. Sam BillingsÂ drives it back to the bowler who half-stops it and the ball goes towards mid off.
Short of a length, around middle. Sam BillingsÂ tucks it with soft hands to the on side for a run. England are underway in the last session.
FOUR! Lovely timing and placement from Woakes! Green serves a full ball, around middle. Woakes prods and just eases it past the mid on fielder to bag a boundary.
Good-length ball, well outside off. Billings does not offer any shot to this one.
Length ball, angling in from middle. Sam BillingsÂ flicks it towards deep mid-wicket and settles for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Chris WoakesÂ leaves it alone watchfully.
This is a length ball, around off, cramping Woakes for room. He does well to tap it towards cover.

BEATEN ALL ENDS UP! Another peach of a delivery from Boland! A length ball, just outside off and shaping away late. Woakes gets stuck in his crease as he tries to push it through the off side. The ball zips past his outside edge.
Good-length ball, around off. Woakes defends it to the off side. End of another probing over from Boland!
This was a length ball, way outside off. Sam BillingsÂ leaves it alone.
Short of a length, around off. Sam BillingsÂ gets behind the line of the ball and blocks it out.
On a length, around middle. Sam BillingsÂ presses forward and defends it to the off side.
JAFFA! Back of a length, just outside off and jagging back in late. Billings stays back to block but the ball sneaks through his bat through to the keeper.
Back of a length, around off. Sam BillingsÂ is solid in his defense this time around.
FOUR! Classy from the debutant! Green serves a half-volley, outside off. Sam BillingsÂ lunges forward and carves it past the mid off fielder for a boundary.

This is just unreal bowling from Boland! A length ball, angled into off and the ball just shapes away ever so beautifully. Woakes is caught on the crease and has a poke at it but gets beaten all ends up yet again.
Shorter in length, over middle. Woakes looks to keep it down off the back foot but the ball goes off the inside edge towards backward square leg. They come back for a couple.
Around the top of off and blocked out.
FOUR! Boland just overpitches and Woakes with a lovely cover drive. Fullish ball, around off and Woakes gets forward to stroke it through the cover region for a boundary.
LEG BYE! Back of a length, at the body. Woakes looks to tuck it away leg side but misses. The ball goes off the thigh pads onto the leg side and they get a leg bye.
FOUR! Edgy boundary! Slightly fuller and outside off, inviting the drive. Billings pushes at it with soft hands and gets an outside edge which runs away to the backward point fence.

SIX! All the way! Woakes thought he was gone for all money but gets just about enough on it. Banged in short, over middle. Woakes has both feet in the air as he hooks it away. The ball carries over the man at the square leg fence for a maximum.
Pitched up, on off and punched back towards the bowler. The big man does well to get low to his left and make a stop.
A good-length ball, angled into middle and leg. Woakes tucks it towards mid-wicket for one.
On off. Solidly blocked out by Billings.

OUT! TAKEN! The plan has worked for AustraliaÂ and they getÂ Sam Billings. A well-directed short ball from Cameron Green, right around the helmet. Billings cannot get out of the way and goes for the pull shot. He is a bit late and the ball goes off the top edgeÂ and flies towards the fine leg fence. Scott BolandÂ takes an easy catch and this opens the floodgates for Australia to wrap things up here.
Howout: c Scott Boland b Cameron Green

Commentary: A length ball, angled into middle. Wood jams it out towards gully and looks for the single but the fielder does well to make the stop.
Play and a miss. To be honest, I don't know how anyone would play that one. Beautifully angled in from around off and the ball just shapes away so perfectly, leaving the batter bamboozled.

FOUR! Another edgy boundary but England will take those at this stage. Length again, outside off. Woakes pushes at it and gets it in between third slip and gully as the ball races towards the third man fence.
Length again, outside off. Woakes has a swing at it but misses.

FOUR BYES! A bit wayward from Scott Boland. It's the inswinger but the ball starts on leg stump and just keeps going further down. Carey dives to his left but can't get to it. The ball races away into the fine leg fence.
A bit width on offer and this is eased towards deep point for one.
Sliding down leg. A fuller delivery, attacking the pads. Wood looks to flick but gets cramped for room and gets struck on the pads.
Cummins is right on the money. Good-length ball, around off and this is angled in. The ball straightens after pitching and Woakes gets squared all ends up.
And again. This time it's even closer to the off pole and Woakes gets beaten past the outside edge.
LEG BYE! Short of a length, at the body. Woakes gets it off the thigh pads on the leg side and gets a leg bye.
On off, Wood stands tall and pushes it through covers for a run.
On a good length, on middle. Chris WoakesÂ makes a bit of room and looks to heave it to the leg side but misses and gets hit in the mid riff.
Flashy shot but no connection. Full, around off. Woakes backs away and swings hard at it but misses it completely.
Good running. Around middle and leg, Wood dabs it towards mid-wicket and scampers through for one.
FOUR! Chris WoakesÂ is profiting in the third man region. Fuller, on middle and pushed across the batter. Woakes edges it past gully and picks up yet another boundary.
Length, on middle. Woakes works it away nicely through mid-wicket and picks up a single.
A length ball, around leg and at 146 kph. Wood looks to tuckÂ it away off his hips but misses and the ball goes off the thigh pads towards deep square leg for one.
Back of a length, over middle. Woakes hops back and keeps it down towards deep square leg for another one.
Good-looking shot. Pitched up, on off, looking to bring it back in. Wood punches it nicely through mid off. The fielder though chases it down and saves a run for his team.
Length ball, angling in from outside off. Wood looks to drive on the up but it goes off the inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
In the air...but it lands safely! Full ball, around leg. Chris WoakesÂ chips it uppishly to wide of the deep mid-wicket fielder for a run.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! A length ball, outside off. Mark WoodÂ prods and smacks it through the vacant cover region for a boundary.
Fuller in length, outside off. Mark WoodÂ looks to drive but the ball zips past his blade.
Cummins bangs it into the deck, around middle. Wood looks to pull but he misses.
On a length, just outside off. Wood lunges forward and pushes it towards the mid off fielder.

Good effort from Nathan LyonÂ in the deep! Length ball, around off. Woakes backs away and drives it past the cover fielder. Lyon runs across to his right and dives just in front of the ropes to save a couple of runs for his side.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! JEEZ! What a review from the Aussies! This was a good-length ball, around leg. Woakes looks to flick but he only manages a tickle, which ricochets off his hips and then goes to the keeper. Alex Carey, behind the sticks makes no mistake and Starc appeals. The umpire says no and Pat CumminsÂ opts for a review. The UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball was passing the bat and Chris WoakesÂ is a goner.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Broad backs away so starc follows him and bowls a yorker, around leg. Stuart BroadÂ fails to dig it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Stuart BroadÂ squeezes it out watchfully.
Whooaa! That missed the off stump by an inch! A low full toss, just outside off. Broad hops in his crease and then looks to block it but he misses.
OUT! CHOPPED ON! This is a very full ball, outside off. Broad looks to dig it out without any feet movement. Broad gets a thick inside edge onto his off stump. EnglandÂ lose their ninth wicket.
Howout: b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Full ball, around off. Wood backs away and drills it towards mid off.
SIX! Whooaa, where did that come from? Full ball, in the slot, around middle. Wood hangs back and sends it sailing way over the long on fence for a maximum.

In the air...but safe! This is a length ball, around off. Wood looks to heave it away but it goes off the outer half of the blade and falls just in front of the cover fielder who runs back to grab it. The batters take a couple.

OUT! BOWLED! Pat CumminsÂ has the last laugh and gets his fourth wicket of the innings.He serves a length ball, around off. Wood hangs back and looks to slogÂ butÂ misses it completely. The ball cannons onto his off stump and EnglandÂ are bundled out for 188!
Howout: b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Lovely start from Stuart Broad. A length ball, outside off and this one just zips away from David WarnerÂ as he looks to block it.
This is angled into middle and leg, Warner watchfully defends it out.

OUT! TAKEN! Stuart BroadÂ has done it again! He proves to be David Warner'sÂ nemesis yet again as Warner walks back on a pair. Length again, this time there's some width on offer. Warner is stuck on the crease and instead of thrashing at it, he looks to work it past backward point. The ball though goes uppishly to the right of point and Ollie PopeÂ flies to his right to grab a stunner. Just the start the visitors were looking for. Can they build on it?
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Well, that swung a long way. Angled in from outside off and the ball ends up going way down the leg side. Sam BillingsÂ does really well to jump to his left and pouch it.
AustraliaÂ are off the mark. Length again, angled at the pads. Marnus LabuschagneÂ flicks it through square leg for a single.
Broad switches to 'round the wicket and delivers a fullish ball, outside off. This one shapes away late but Khawaja make an easy leave.
On a good length, in that channel around off.Â Labuschagne goes back and forth to block and gets beaten by the away movement.
Woakes hits the length hard, around off andÂ Labuschagne keeps it down on the off side.
That one nipped back in sharply. A length ball, around off and ends up around middle and leg.Â Labuschagne looks to block but gets hit on the body.
Woakes goes full and bowls it on off.Â Labuschagne jams it out.
Peach! Woakes goes slightly fuller, around off. The batter is drawn forward and hye gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball shapes away beautifully.

Oh, careful there Rory Burns. Back of a length, on off.Â Labuschagne squeezes it through the gully region and Burns chases it down. Just as Burns slides, he gets his foot stuck in the turf. Three taken.
On middle. Blocked out.

Misfield and Broad ventsÂ his frustration. Around that fourth stump line and once againÂ Labuschagne is drawn forward a bit. He plays it with soft hands towards point, where the fielder fumbles and allows a single.
Close! A length ball, hurled across from 'round the wicket and angled into off stump. Khawaja makes an assured leave.
Slightly fuller and wider, left alone by Khawaja.
An action replay of the previous delivery as this one shapes away from outside off. Khawaja doesn't play at it.
Length ball, outside off and left alone.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The dangerman, Marnus LabuschagneÂ is sent packing early. A length ball, around middle and angling down the leg side.Â Labuschagne shuffles across his stumps a bit and just like the first innings, that's his undoing.Â Labuschagne looks to flick it fine but gets a slight tickle on it and Sam BillingsÂ springs to his left to take a great catch. That's his first catch in Test cricket and boy, the whole team is pumped up for him. Root shakes his hand and maybe, just maybe EnglandÂ have an opportunity here.
Howout: c Sam Billings b Chris Woakes

Commentary: Smith is on a pair and just about manages to fend this one away. A length ball, attacking middle and leg. Smith keeps it out.
Around the top of middle and blocked out by Smith.
Smith is off the mark and he will be mightily relieved. Good-length ball, outside off and shaping away. This one bounces a bit extra but Smith is able to work it through covers for a single.
Fullish ball, on off and shaping in. Khawaja blocks it out.
A length ball, close to the off stump and Khawaja makes a good leave.
This is angled into middle. Smith goes across his crease and works it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Slightly fuller, sliding onto the pads. Smith punches it towards mid on.
Good take. Broad spills this one well down the leg side and Billings does well to dive to his left and pouch that one.
Broad goes full and looks to skid one through bat and pad. Smith goes back and forth to keep it out. Lovely footwork from Smith though.
A length ball, swinging down the leg side. Left alone by Smith.
Wow, that one just kept on going down leg. A cross-seamer probably from Broad, on a length and angled down leg. The ball goes further down leg and Smith makes a stylish leave.
Length delivery, around off. Usman KhawajaÂ presses forward and keeps it out watchfully.
Back of a length, just outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ does not offer any shot to this one.

NOT OUT! Usman KhawajaÂ ESCAPES! Top delivery nonetheless from Woakes! This was on a length, around middle and shaping away a bit. Khawaja stays back to block but he misses and the ball just clips his pad before going to the keeper. Joe RootÂ opts for a review very late but the Ball Tracker indicates that there was no bat involved and EnglandÂ lose a review.
Good-length ball, outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ leaves it alone.
Length ball, on middle. Usman KhawajaÂ defends it towards mid on.
Fuller in length, way outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, angling in from middle. Steven SmithÂ looks to leave it but the ball hits him high on his body.
On a length, nipping back in from off. Steven SmithÂ glances it towards fine leg for a run.
Broad comes 'round the wicket and serves a length delivery, outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ makes an assured leave.
Good-length ball, around off. Usman KhawajaÂ prods and blocks it out.
Short of a length, jagging back in down leg. Khawaja misses his flick as the ball goes through to the keeper.
This one was on a length, well outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
FOUR! An appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested! Good-length ball, angling in from off. Smith looks to flick but he gets an inside edge onto his pads and it races away to the fine leg fence.
Length ball, outside off. Steven SmithÂ leaves it alone.
Short of a length, around off. Steven SmithÂ hangs back and blocks it to the off side.
A slight mix-up but no harm done! Good-length ball, just outside off. Steven SmithÂ stands tall and taps it to the off side. He takes off for a run but it sent back by Khawaja.
FOUR! No need to run for these kindÂ of shots! Fuller in length, outside off. Smith lunges forward and caresses it through the vacant region for a boundary.
On a length, around off. Steven SmithÂ defends it out.
Good-length ball, nipping back in down leg. Usman KhawajaÂ misses his flick this time.
Leg bye! Short of a length, jagging back in late from outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ misses his tuck on the leg side and gets hit near his thigh pad. The batters sneak in a leg bye.
Back of a length, outside off and nipping back in late. Smith leaves it alone watchfully.
Fuller in length, well outside off. Steven SmithÂ prods but does not offer any shot to this one.
BEATEN! Top delivery from Broad! Good-length ball, around the fifth stump channel. Smith has a poke at it but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Good-length ball, angling in from outside off. Smith presses forward to block and yells 'NO RUN'.
On a length, just outside off and angling across the batter. Usman KhawajaÂ looks to defend but the ball goes past his blade.
Fuller this time, oustdie off. Usman KhawajaÂ pushes it towards mid off.
Woakes drags his length back, outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ shoulders his arms to this one.
BEATEN! Back of a length, around middle and going on with the angle. Usman KhawajaÂ looks to block but he misses.
AND AGAIN! Length ball, around off and curling away late. Usman KhawajaÂ looks to defend but the ball whistles past his blade.
Banged into the deck, around middle. Usman KhawajaÂ stays back and pulls it along the ground towards fine leg. He finally gets off the mark and gets a loud cheer from the crowd!
Back of a length, angling in from outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ looks to block but he misses and gets hit near his thigh pad.
FOUR! Uppish but safe! Full ball, outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ looks for a booming drive but it goes off the outer half of the blade past the backward point fielder for a boundary.
Length ball, outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from off. Usman KhawajaÂ blocks it out solidly.
Another ball, on a length, around middle. Usman KhawajaÂ gets behind the line of the ball to defend.
Fuller in length, outside off. Usman KhawajaÂ lets it through to the keeper.
Robinson starts with a length ball, around off. Smith shuffles across and blocks it out towards point.
A bit fuller this time, outside off. Smith does not offer any shot to this one.
Back of a length, around off. Steven SmithÂ stays back to defend.

FOUR! A bit streaky from Smith and he is lucky that the ball did not go straight to the leg slip fielder. Back of a length, around middle and leg. Smith looks to shoulder his arms to it but the ball just brushes his gloves and goes in between the diving keeper and the leg slip fielder for a boundary.
Good-length ball, around off. Steven SmithÂ blocks it out.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head! Fuller in length, outside off. Smith prods but does not offer any shot to this one. The ball hits him low on his pad.
Wood comes 'round the wicket and starts off with a gentle half-volley, on the pads. Khawaja clips it towards deep square leg and picks up a couple.

Was there an edge? Was it LBW? Peach of a delivery from Wood. A length ball, angled into off and middle. The ball just seams away after pitching. Khawaja gets squared up and the ball just clips the back leg and goes to the keeper. Huge shouts from the visitors but nothing given. The replay shows that it did hit the pads and was just a bit high.
FOUR! Mark WoodÂ has had absolutely no luck in this series. Around the top of off and the outside edge is found yet again. The ball keeps low off the bat and runs down into the third man fence.
Back of a length, on off. Khawaja hops to keep it down.
A length ball, angled into middle and leg. Khawaja manages to keep it out.
Length again, angled into off. Khawaja defends it solidly off the front foot.
Good-length ball, over the leg stump. Smith shuffles across yet again and looks to flick but misses.
Back of a length, nipping back in from around off. Smith gets caught on the crease and gets hit high on the pads.
This one is sliding on the pads, Smith looks to leave but gets rapped on the pads.
It's not easy out there at the moment. A lot of inside edges and balls hitting the pads. A length ball, on off and angling in. Smith looks to push at it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Robinson is bowling a good length but given his height, the ball's always going over the stumps. Good-length ball, angled into leg stump and Smith gets hit on the pads yet again.
On middle. Blocked out.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! That is a brute of a delivery from Mark Wood. Wood bends his back and angles in a pacy short delivery at 147.7 kph. The ball is directed right at the helmet and given the sting on the ball,Â Usman KhawajaÂ had almost no chance of getting out of the way. Khawaja did try but just couldn't keep his bat down. The ball just comes off the gloves and Sam BillingsÂ takes a sharp catch to his right. EnglandÂ are looking for more wickets here.
Howout: c Sam Billings b Mark Wood

Commentary: This is a fiery spell from Wood. A length ball, around 146 kph and on off. Boland does well to get a ball on it.
Ooh, that one just whizzed past the helmet. Another short ball, around off and at 142 kph. Boland ducks down to get away from it but almost get nailed on the head.
Back of a length, on off. Boland hops to defend and that is probably a much easier length to defend for a nightwatchman.
A length ball, around off and kept out on the off side by Boland.
Boland is off the mark. Around the top of off, edged down with soft hands through backward point and they get one. Scott BolandÂ will retain strike.
Robinson hits the length hard and bowls it outside off. Boland taps it back onto the deck.
Slightly fuller this time, on off. Boland gets his bat right behind the line of the ball to block.
Just a bit too high yet again. On a length, around off and this one just nips back in off the surface. Boland gets caught on the crease and gets pinged on the pads as well.
Shortish ball, outside off and shaping away. Boland doesn't play at it.
Full, on middle. Boland manages to block it out.
A length ball, on middle and angling in. Boland looks to keep it out but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Sliding down leg this one.
On a good length, on off and angled in. Smith hops back to defend.
Back of a length, around the hips. Steven SmithÂ shuffles across and works it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Well bowled. A length ball, angled in from outside off but this one shapes away after pitching and zips past the outside edge.

Uppish but safe! Wood hits the length hard at 143 kph and bowls it on off stump. Scott BolandÂ is pushed on the back foot as he tries to fend it away. The ball comes off the handle of the bat but falls safely around silly mid off.
Around the top of off and this is edged down through backward point for a run.
Banged in short but spilled down the leg side. Steven SmithÂ isn't interested in playing that one.
Slightly pitched up, outside off and just moving away off the seam. Boland makes an easy leave.

Ooh! Sam BillingsÂ has the ball up in the air and looks like he's certain. The ball is pitched up and is angled into off stump. The ball straightens after pitching and whizzes past the outside edge of Boland's bat. Joe RootÂ has a think about it but decides against it. The replay shows that the ball missed the bat.
Length again, around middle and Boland keeps it out.
Fuller in length, angled at the pads. Boland looks to flick but the ball skids through and gets hit on the pads.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. This is worked through square leg for a single by Boland.
On off and angling back in sharply. Smith keeps it out on the leg side.

That is a sore one! A spicy short ball, on the body. Boland tries his best to fend it away but gets hit flush on the index finger. He seems to be in some pain but the physio isn't out on the field. The physio does eventually come out but the umpire sends him back as he feels the batter is trying to make the most of it.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Boland manages to keep it down.
A length ball, on middle and Boland gets bat on it yet again.
Well played by Boland. On a good length, angled at the body and Boland manages to keep it down.
Just short! A fiery bumper, around middle and leg. The ball hurries onto Boland as he looks to keep it at bay. The ball hits the gloves and loops up but falls well short of leg gully.

Boland survives! Well bowled and well played! Mark WoodÂ puts everything in this last delivery and gets in the yorker on middle at 145 kph. Scott BolandÂ just about manages to get his bat down in time to jam it out towards short leg. A brilliant end to the day as AustraliaÂ finish the day on 36/3 and they lead by 152 runs.
Broad starts with a length ball, landing wide outside off and coming back in. Smith leaves it alone though.
A bit of away shape on that but this starts way outside off. Smith shoulders arms yet again.
Another one that shapes away from the sixth stump. Smith is yet to offer a stroke on Day 3.
This is fuller, just outside off. Smith prods forward and taps it towards mid off.
Nice and full, on off. Smith pushes it to mid on.
Maiden to start the day. Length ball, around off. Smith looks to work it away to the leg side but gets it off the outer half back to the bowler.
Wood hurls a length ball, on off. Boland stays in the crease to block it out.
A bumper by Wood but way down the leg side. Boland leaves it and Billings moves to his left to collect it.

The batters run four! Full, on middle. Boland nicely punches it down the ground. But the ball slows down as it approaches the fence. Broad gives the long chase to stop the ball just inside the ropes. But the batters have enough time to run four!
On a length, on off. Blocked out.

Full and wide outside off. Boland goes for the drive but gets the outside edge. The ball flies very low to the left of Burns at gully. He dives that side and gets his hands to the ball. Don't think that carried to him. The ball is deflected away and the batters take one.
Length, on the pads. Smith works it past mid-wicket for a single.
Length, on middle and leg. Smith misses the flick and gets hit on the pads.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Smith goes for the drive with his hands but gets a thick inside edge back on the pads.
FOUR! Nicely done by Smith! Broad goes full and targets the pads in the hope that Smith will miss it. But Smith clips it nicely and the ball races to the square leg fence.

He misses this time! Broad looked very excited about that but Root reckons it was too high! Length ball, lands on middle. Smith misses the flick and gets hit near the knee roll. There is a big appeal by Broad and he looks convinced but the umpire is not. Root walks up to have a word with the pacer but the English skipper reckons that it is too high and decides not to review. Good decision as Ball Tracker shows that it was going over.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.

Big appeal again! Ooh, this is much closer! This time Broad goes full and around off. Smith rarely misses these balls but twice in the same over, he gets struck on the pads while looking to work it away. Broad is convinced again, well he always is convinced! But to be fair, this is a good appeal. The umpire turns it down again and Root after thinking about it for a while, decides not to review. Impact could have been an issue there.
Back of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Bumper, on off. Boland sits under it.

OUT! TAKEN! Gone this time! A faint edge and Scott BolandÂ has to walk back! Well bowled by Wood. He bowls a bumper, right at the body. It is a rising one too and too good for the nightwatchman. Boland looks to keep it out but gets a thin edge back to the keeper. Billings does it with ease and Boland's resilience ends. He has done his job well though.
Howout: c Sam Billings b Mark Wood

Commentary: Short of a length, on the body. Head works it aerially towards where a short leg would have been. But there is no one there.
Back of a length again, on the body. Head works it towards square leg for one.
Length ball, around off. Smith blocks it with ease.
Length ball, around off. Head drives it to deep cover for one.
On a length, just outside off. Smith blocks it from the crease.
Full, on middle. Smith gets it off the inner half past square leg for one. 50 up for the hosts.
Stays a bit low! Length ball, angling across off. Head goes for the cut but misses it. The ball dies down on its way to the keeper.
FOUR! Top shot! Full by Broad again, on off. Head nicely punches it down the ground. Broad dives to his left but cannot get there and the ball runs to the fence.
Beaten! A touch shorter and angling across off. Head is stuck in the crease while looking to block and the ball zips past the outside edge.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Short and on the body. Smith pulls it along the ground to deep square leg for one.
A sharp short one, on the body. Head ducks under it though.
Well bowled! A bumper, on the body again. Head hops up looking to work it away but gets hit on the shoulder of the bat. It lands near him though and doesn't pop up.
Very full and around leg. Head looks to flick it away but gets hit on the pads. There is a mild appeal but it was pitching outside leg.
Wood is back to banging it short, on middle. Head blocks it well.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.

Fired full, on the pads. Smith misses the flick and gets hit on the pads. There is a bit of an appeal by Broad but he suggests that there was a bit of bat on it. Good call as the umpire gives it as runs and the replays confirm the same. Billings has a burst of energy and has a few words of encouragement for the bowler.
Length, outside off. Left alone.
Full and a bit wider. Head drives it uppishly, to the left of deep cover for a couple.
Play and a miss! Broad drags his length back a bit and angles it across off. Head goes for the drive but is beaten on the outside edge.
Length and around leg. Head gets struck on the pads as he misses his glance. The ball rolls away to the leg side and the batters get a leg bye. A mild appeal again, but this is pitching outside leg.
Back of a length, around off. Tapped to covers.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Wood gets his third! It is Broad who is going past the edges, getting the ball to hit the batters on the pads and Wood is reaping the rewards with his short bowling! A short one, down the leg side. Head shuffles a bit inside the line to workÂ it away but gets a faint tickle on it. There is a noise as the ball passes the bat and Billings does the rest behind the stumps. The umpire obliges this time and gives Head his marching orders. A really good morning for England so far but they will need to finish this off quickly. Cameron GreenÂ is the new man at the crease.
Howout: c Sam Billings b Mark Wood

Commentary: Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Too short and down the leg side. Green lets it go way over him. Billings gets to his left to gather it. Wide called. That was too high!
Wood comes 'round the stumps and bowls a short one, on off. Green gets low but not low enough. The ball hits his shoulder.
This time Green ducks low enough to let the ball go over him.
A bumper, down the leg side. Green ducks under it yet again. A really good over by Wood!
On a length, on off. Smith blocks it out.
Fired full, on middle. Smith works it past square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.

Well bowled! Length ball, landing on off and coming back in. Green leaves a gap between his bat and pad. The ball sneaks through that and hits him on the pads. Broad appeals yet again but not given. Ball Tracker shows it was going way over the off stumps.

Appeal again by Broad! Length and on the pads. Green gets hit on the pads but it is likely sliding down the leg stump and could be too high too. It rolls away to the leg side and the batters cross over. Broad puts in a toned-down appeal this time but the umpire says no.
Full, on the pads. Worked away past square leg for one.
Back of a length, outside off. Pushed to covers.

OUT! TAKEN! GONE GONE GONE! Smith is gone and Wood is delighted! I would be too if I got Smith out and took 4 wickets against the Aussies! But Wood has been sensational with the ball and he has deserved this. One would say that he has deserved a lot more wickets but hasn't got them! The barrage of short deliveries continues from Wood and he bowls a sharp one at Smith's body. Smith shuffles a bit inside the line looking to pull but he can'tÂ keep it on the ground as he gets the top edge.Â The ball goes straight to fine leg and Dawid MalanÂ takes an easy catch.
Howout: c Dawid Malan b Mark Wood

Commentary: Short ball, down the leg side. Left alone.
Bumper, on off. Carey ducks under it.
Another short one and Carey ducks.

Would have been a run out! Wood comes 'round the wicket and bowls a length ball, on middle. Carey works it to the leg side and sets off. Green though is watching the ball and is very slow to react.Â The man at mid-wicket moves to his left, gathers the ball and has a shy at the batter's end. The ball misses the stumps though. Green would have been out had the ball hit.
Full, on off. Blocked out.
Full, on the pads. Flicked to fine leg for a couple.
Fuller, on off. Worked to mid on.

A length ball, around middle and leg. Carey flicks it to the left of mid on.Â Stuart BroadÂ over there makes a really good stop and gets in the direct hit at the bowler's end. The batters though cross over comfortably.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Full, on off. Pushed past covers for a couple. Nicely played by Green there.
Back of a length, around off and angling across. Carey hangs deep and bunts it down on the off side for a quick single. Green once again hesitates but they get through for one.
Wood hits the length hard and bowls it around the off pole. Green dabs it down towards covers.
On a good length, angled into middle and at 144 kph. Green gets right behind the line of the ball to block.
Wood comes from 'round the wicket this time and angles a short ball at the body. Green hops and keeps it down towards backward square leg for a single.
What was Carey looking to do there? Carey shuffles right across his stumps and Wood fires in a quick, fuller delivery around middle. Carey just about manages to keep it out on the leg side.
Banged in from 'round the stumps and going over middle. Carey ducks under it.
Pitched up, on off. This is punched back towards the bowler.
A length ball, outside off and left alone by Green.
Slightly fuller, angled into middle. Green defends it solidly off the back foot.
Just a fraction short, on middle. Green tucks it through square leg and picks up a single.
Good-length ball, on leg. Carey works it behind square on the leg side for a couple.
On off. This is pushed towards the cover region.
Good-length ball, around off and nipping in off the seam. Green looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads as the ball goes towards the slip cordon.
Right around the top of off and nipping back in sharply. Green looks to defend off the front foot but gets an inisde edge onto the pads.
Slightly fuller, around off and nipping in late. Green makes a leave.
That's the second time Green's got an inside edge onto the pads and there's not a fielder forÂ bat-pad yet. A good-length ball, around off and Green looks to block but inside edges it onto the pads.
Around the off pole and blocked out.
A touch fuller, around off and nipping in late. Green makes the leave. A maiden over from Woakes.
Well bowled. Fullish ball, on off and sliding across the left-hander. Carey looks to push at it but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Around middle and leg, Carey strides forward to defend but gets an inside edge past short leg. They get a single.
Length again, outside off. Green shoulders arms.
On a good length, wide of off stump. Green taps it on the off side and picks up a quick single.
Fuller delivery, on off. Carey prods and pushes it on the off side for a quick single. There should not have been a run there to be honest.
FOUR! That will release a lot of pressure. On the pads and flicked away fine by Green into the fine leg fence.

FOUR! Carey gets a juicy half-volley, outside off and he is able to stroke it away through covers for another boundary. Australia's lead reaches 200 now. An interesting phase coming up now. Wonder how the Aussies will approach the game now. Anything over 250 could be a big task for England to chase in the final innings.
FOUR! And again! A tad too full, around off. Carey drives it through cover-point this time and the ball races away to the fence.
In that channel around off and beating the bat of Carey.
Almost chopped on! On a good length, around the off pole. Carey looks to stride forward but gets an inside edge back onto the pads.
On off. Blocked out on the off side.
Woakes goes fuller, around off. Carey drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
Back of a length, around the hips. Carey pulls it past short leg.
A length ball, on off and sliding across. Carey presses forward to defend.
Robinson hits the length hard, on middle. Carey hangs back to block.
Beaten! Robinson goes fuller, on off and the ball's going across. Carey is pushed forward as he looks to keep it out and the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
A touch fuller again, on middle. Carey defends it out solidly.
A length ball, around off. Carey works it towards covers and sets off for a quick single.
Around off. Defended off the front foot.

NO BALL! Big, big moment in the match but the rub of the green goes Carey's way. A shortish ball, around off. Alex CareyÂ looks to pull but sort of falls over and ends up getting an inside edge back onto the stumps. The third umpire checks for a no ball and unfortunately for England, Chris WoakesÂ doesn't have anything behind the line and the visitors cannot believe it. A huge let off.
On a good length, around off and kept out by Carey.
Woakes goes fuller, on off. Carey pushes it past mid off for a single.
A length ball, around off and angling in. Green strides forward to defend.
Edged away! Back of a length, around off. Cameron GreenÂ hops back to defend but gets a thick outside edge past the slip cordon. The fielder chases it down but they come back for the third.
Slightly shorter, around off and worked past backward point for one.
Fuller, on off. Blocked back to the bowler.
On a length, angling across off. Left alone.
Fuller, on off. Carey goes for the drive but gets the inside edge on the pads.
Nicely defended out by Carey again.
Beaten! This lands on a length, on off and comes back in a bit. Carey is beaten on the inside edge while looking to block.
Length, on off. Carey takes a step down the track to block it out.
A length ball, at the hips. Green tucks it around the corner and picks up a couple down to deep square leg.
On a good length, angled into off and this one holds its line after pitching. Green makes a watchful block off the back foot.
Full and straight, Green punches it back towards the bowler who does well to get his hand to it.
Over middle, Green stands tall and works it through mid-wicket for a single. The 100 is up for Australia now and the lead is stretched to 215 already.
On off. Blocked out.
A length ball, around leg. Carey looks to tuck it away but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards backward square leg. They get one.
A touch fuller, on off. Carey defends it back to the bowler.
Right around the top of off. Blocked out off the back foot.
Robinson goes fuller, around off and middle. Carey is brought forward to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Lovely delivery! Perfect length, on off and angling away from the left-hander. Carey has a poke at it but the ball zips past the outside edge.
A length ball, on off. Carey taps it back onto the deck.
On a good length this time, outside off. Carey taps it towards point. A maiden over from Robinson.
Length, around off. Green gets the inside edge on the pads.
Beaten again! Fuller, around off. Green goes for the drive but it zips past the outside edge.
Again! On a length, just outside off. Green takes a stride forward to block and it goes past the outside edge.
Full, on off. Pushed down the ground. Woakes gets his right hand down and gets his hand to it and half-stops it.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
A solid front-foot defence by Green to end the over.
Length, on off. Tapped to the leg side.
Shorter, outside off. Slapped towards cover.
On a length, around off. Carey blocks it out.
Jaffa! Fuller, angling across off. Carey looks to work it away to the leg side but is beaten.
Nicely played. Length, just outside off. Carey nicely works it past backward point for a couple.
Full, on off. Blocked out to mid off.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Blocked out by Green.
FOUR! More runs to third man and no luck for England! Length ball, on off. Green gets the outside edge but it drops just short of the man at second slip and runs to the fence.
Nicely driven down the ground but the man at mid off dives and stops it.
Beaten again! Fuller, fifth-stump line. Green looks to drive it away but it zips past the outside edge.
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone.

FOUR! And yet another boundary down to third man! Full, around off. Green gets the outside edge again. This time the ball goes along the ground and past the slip cordon for a boundary. Frustration is clearly visible on the face of Woakes.
Full, on the pads. Flicked away nicely to deep mid-wicket for one.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Nicely pushed to mid off.
On a length, around off. Green works it to mid-wicket.

OUT! LBW! Broad finally gets his man! He has deserved a wicket for the way he has bowled this morning! The 49-run stand is broken and England needed this big time. Length ball, on off. Green gets forward to block but the ball nips away a bit and Green gets hit on the pads. Broad puts on a celebrappeal - meaning that he is celebrating even before the decision is made! But the umpire is not convinced and there are also overthrows when someone throws the ball and misses the stumps. Root decides to review this one. No bat on that and Ball Tracker has the ball smashing into the off pole after hitting in line!
Howout: lbw b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, on middle. Carey taps it past square leg for a single.
Short and down the leg side, left alone.Â A rare mistake by Billings as he fails to gather the ball after diving to his right. Bye taken.

Review not taken! Shorter and down the leg side. Carey looks to work it away but misses. There is a noise as the ball goes past him and Billings takes it. An appeal follows from the keeper and the bowler but the umpire is unmoved. The English players get together but Stokes from square leg yells 'JUMPER! JUMPER!' to suggest that it hit the sweater of Carey. Good decision as the replays confirm the same.
Back of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, outside off. Carey works it past point for a couple.
A nasty bumper, on the body. Carey gets hit on the glovesÂ as he looks to block awkwardly and the ball falls around short leg.
Length, on the paads. Starc works it past square leg for one.
Length ball, outside off. Carey pushes it wide of gully for a single.

NOT OUT! Pitching outside leg! Celebrappeal does not work for Broad this time and Carey gets lucky again! Length ball, landing around leg. Carey looks to block but gets hit on the pads. Broad is running in celebration already and the umpire raises the finger! But Carey reviews it. No bat on that. But, but, the ball is pitching just outside leg. Just outside leg and by that I mean millimeters outside leg! All that Root can do is have a wry smile.
Length ball, on the pads. Worked through square leg for a couple.
Length, on off. Blocked out.
Full, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! TAKEN! No review needed this time and the workhorse, Wood, gets his third 5-wicket haul in Tests! He has been a sensational bowler for England and has deserved each and every one of these wickets! He soaks in the applause from the crowd and Australia lose their eighth wicket. A bumper, on the body of Starc. He looks to block but gets the inside edge on the thigh padÂ and straight to short leg. Ollie PopeÂ takes it with ease.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Mark Wood

Commentary: NOT OUT! Missing the off stump by millimeters and Australia get lucky yet again! Cummins has a nice laugh about it but noneÂ of the English players are smiling. Corker of a yorker by Wood though. He comes 'round the wicket with Cummins probably expecting a short one. Cummins is already ducking a bit and Wood fires a yorker, right on the boot. Cummins fails to dig it out and gets hit on the boot. Up goes the finger butÂ Cummins reviews it! No bat on that again, but since Wood is bowling 'round the stumps, the angle could take the ball away from the off pole. Yes, it is! Missing off stump by millimeters. Not even clipping the stump!
Shorter in length, down the leg side. Left alone.
And again! Short and outside leg. Cummins isn't interested in playing at that one.
Another one that is full and fast, across the off stump. It is a bit wider this time but Cummins can't get any bat on it.
Wood comes over the wicket now and angles in a short ball, on the body. Cummins hops and keeps it down towards square leg for a single.
There's still a lot of movement off the pitch here. A length ball, outside off and this one shapes in late and just goes past the off stump as Cummins makes the leave.
Fullish ball, around off and pushed out on the off side.
A length ball, angled into middle and leg. Cummins defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length, around off and seaming back in. Cummins looks to defend off the back foot but gets a blow around the chest area.
On a good length, around off. Cummins hangs back to block it on the off side.
This one is sliding onto the pads, Cummins looks to flick but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards square leg. They cross for one and look for the second but don't go for it.

FOUR! Well played and that's valuable runs for the hosts. Back of a length, angled across the right-hander. Cummins hangs deep and just opens the face of the bat to guide it towards the backward point fence.

Ouch! That looked nasty! A quick short ball, angled at the body. Cummins tries to fend it away but gets hit flush on the left glove. The ball pops up and falls safely around leg gully. They get a run.
Carey backs away and Wood follows him with a length ball. Carey looks to heave it away to the leg side but gets an inside edge back onto the pads.
Attempted short ball, down the leg side. Carey lets it go past him.
Wood looks to bounce Carey out with a quick bumper. Carey though does well to get inside the line and pulls it along the ground towards fine leg for a single.
Just wide! Short of a good length, on the body. Cummins hops and tucks it just past short leg for another single.
Right around the top of off. Pat CumminsÂ stays solid in defense.
A length ball, on off. Cummins makes a bit of room and swats it across towards dep mid-wicket. Woakes runs around from the square leg fence and keeps it down to a couple.
Good running! The man at mid off was right on the edge of the circle and Cummins takes advantage of that. Slightly fuller, on off and driven on the up towards mid off for a single.

The lead now goes past 250 and with every run scored, England will be feeling more and more anxious. Good-length ball, pushed across the left-hander. Carey edges it down towards the third man fence and picks up three runs.
Vicious bounce this time from Broad! Banged in, around off. Cummins is taken aback by it. He still manages to keep it down on the leg side and even picks up a single.

FOUR! Well played by Carey and Australia end the session on a high. Around middle and leg, this is flicked through mid-wicket for a boundary. At the Dinner interval, Australia are 141/8 and they lead by 256 runs.
Bumper, on middle. Cummins gets hit on the pad but it baloons and falls short of short leg.
OUCH! That will sting! Short and on the body. Cummins looks to duck but he does so very awkwardly. The ball misses the bat and hits his arm.
Back of a length, around off. Cummins hops up to block but is beaten.
On the body again. Cummins gets hit on the pads and it rolls to the leg side.
Nicely done by Cummins as he ducks under this one well.
On a length for the first time in the over. Outside off and Cummins is beaten while looking to block.
Well played. Shorter and angling across off. Carey punches it to deep backward point for a couple.
Back of a length, around off and blocked out.
Nice and full, on off. Carey gets forward to block it.
Fuller, on off. Carey is once again solid in blocking it.
Broad goes full, angling away. Carey taps it past cover for one.
Fuller, on off. Cummins blocks it off the front foot.
Bumper down the leg side. Carey leaves it with ease by moving inside the line of the ball.
This time Carey sits under the ball. Watch out for the yorker probably.
Back of a length, wide outside off. Carey leaves it.
FOUR! Lovely stroke! Short and just outside off. Carey backs away a bit and then carves it over covers for a boundary.
Short again, down the leg side. Left alone by Carey.
Back of a length, wide enough for Carey to leave it.
Length ball, on off. Cummins blocks it off the front foot.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
On a length, on off. Cummins taps it past cover for one.
Nicely driven by Carey to deep cover. 150 up for AustraliaÂ and the lead is 265. Carey moves to 48 too.
Short and on the body. Cummins sits under it.
Short of a length, on off. Cummins rises and taps it towards cover.
Shorter, outside off. Left alone by Carey.
Bumper on the body and Carey sits under it.
Wood comes 'round the wicket and bowls a length ball, down the leg side. Carey leaves it.
Shorter, around off. Carey taps it towards point. He thinks off a single for a moment but decides against it in the end.
Length ball, on middle. Carey gets the inside edge past short leg. They don't take the single though.
A single now! Short and on off. Carey taps it towards cover for an easy singe. He moves to 49.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! GONE THIS TIME! After surviving a couple of close calls, Alex CareyÂ walks off on 49! He batted well though. Made those reprives count and put on a good recovery towards the end. This is full and way, way outside off. Carey goes at it with his hands only. The ball goes past the inside edge and there is a faint edge. Billings takes a good low catch and there is an appeal. Carey stands his ground for a moment but walks off just after the finger is raised. No review this time!
Howout: c Sam Billings b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Length, outside off. Lyon misses the drive.
A huge cheer as Lyon gets off the mark! Full, on middle. He works it towards deep backward square leg for a couple.

Two more! Length, on off. Lyon thumps it down the ground. past the dive of Broad. Burns dives from mid off but gets his knee on the ball. It is deflected away and the batters get a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Full, on off. Driven down the ground again but Broad dives and stops it.
Length, around off. Tapped towards gully.
Cummins backs away to the leg side so Wood fires it full and wide outside off. Cummins fails to dig it out.
Short and down the leg side. Cummins misses the pull. A polite inquiry by Wood to the umpire but nothing doing.

OUT! CASTLED! Career-best figures for Mark Wood! Finally, it feels like he has been rewarded for his efforts! Length ball, on off. Cummins goes for the massive heave but connects only with the thin air around his bat. The ball shatters the stumps. Wood leads his team off the field and soaks in the applause from this Hobart crowd. That ends the innings and AustraliaÂ are bowled out for 155!
Howout: b Mark Wood

Commentary: Starc steams in first ball but spills it down the leg side. Burns looks for the flick but misses.

FOUR! Edgy boundary but Rory BurnsÂ is up and running. Starc angles this one in at off stump and the ball straightens after pitching. Burns gets squared up but luckily for him, the outside edge drops short and goesÂ between third slip and gully for a boundary. He is off the pair. The change of hair has worked!
Good-length ball, angled into the body. Burns looks to tuck it away leg side but the ball just zips through and catches Burns in the mid riff.
Fuller one, at 144 kph and on off. Burns stands tall and drives it past extra cover for a single.
Starc looks to attack the pads and puts a bit extra behind this one as he bowls it around 147 kph. He spills it well down the leg side though.

FOUR LEG BYES! Just hasn't got his rhythm right yet,Â Mitchell Starc. On the pads again and Zak CrawleyÂ goes for the flick. The ball goes off the pads and races away into the fine leg fence. So, 9 off the first over. A positive start for the visitors.
A good-length ball, angled across the off stump. Burns makes an assured leave.
Cummins goes fuller and pushes it across the off stump. The ball is around 133 kph but this one just zips through and has good carry on it as well.
A touch shorter in length, around leg. Burns gets cramped for room and hit on the thigh pad.
Around the top of off and Burns hangs back to defend.
Length again, just a little bit wider. Burns edges it down through backward point with soft hands and picks up a couple.
Pitched up, in that channel around the off stump. This one holds its line but Burns makes an assured leave yet again.
Maybe just nipping back in a bit too much. A length ball, on middle and shaping back in. Crawley looks to punch it back but gets an inside edge onto the pads and that's what saved him.
Around the off stump and looking to bring it back in. Crawley shoulders arms.
A touch fuller and wider, at 149 kph. Crawley isn't interested in playing at that one.
Zak CrawleyÂ is off the mark. Over middle, Crawley wrists it towards fine leg for a single. A big cheer from the crowd as Boland collects the ball. Familiar scenes now.
This is angled at the pads and swinging away. Burns looks to play it square but again looks to be falling over and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but not a big appeal.
Well bowled. Starc surprises Burns with a really full delivery, on middle and shaping away. Burns does well to get a bat on it.
Slightly fuller, around off. Crawley in two minds and decides to leave it at the last second. The ball comes off the toe end of the bat and drops dead near Crawley.
Around the fifth-stump line and an easy leave for Crawley.

FOUR! Edged and just past third slip! A lovely delivery angled into middle and straightening awayÂ after pitching. Crawley gets squared up and the outside edge is found. The ball flies past Usman Khawaja's diveÂ at third slip and races away into the fence.

That would have to be swinging in a mile to get the LBW decision. An in-dipper this time from Cummins. This one pitches well outside off and Crawley just strides out but offers no shot. The ball hits the pads but the umpire isn't interested.
On off. Defended off the front foot.
Ooh, that one did swing in a mile. Cummins bowls this one from wider of the crease and the ball swings in late as Crawley makes the leave.
Pitched up, on middle. Burns blocks it out.

Anxious moment out there in the middle and the last thing the visitors need is another run out. Back of a length, Burns is on the back foot and gets a bottom edge back onto the deck. Crawley looks for the single but Burns doesn't even know where the ball is. Crawley retreats in time.
Good-length, angled into middle and leg. Burns gets caught on the crease and gets pinged on the thigh pad.
FOUR! Nicely put away. Starc goes full and at the pads. Burns flicks it through the vacant mid-wicket region and picks up a boundary.
Short of a length, well outside off. Rory Burns'Â eyes lit up as he looks to thrash it away but just that hint of away movement and he gets beaten past the outside edge.
On a length, around off and left alone.
Sharp work! Cummins hits the length hard and bowls it on off. Crawley taps it straight to Travis HeadÂ at short leg, who keeps Crawley on his toes.
FOUR! Lovely timing from Zak Crawley. Full and angling into middle and leg. Crawley plays an exquisite on drive and picks up a boundary down to the long on fence.
Nicely bowled! A length ball, angled into off and just nibbling away off the pitch. Crawley gets beaten past the outside edge as the ball keeps a bit low as well.
Back of a length, around middle and tapped towards mid-wicket.
Slightly fuller, on off and this is pushed towards mid on.
Good-length ball, angled at the body. Crawley looks to work it away leg side but misses. The ball comes off the pads and lands in front of short leg.
Good-looking shot from Rory Burns. A touch fuller, on off. Burns hangs back and punches it through the cover region. Marnus LabuschagneÂ hunts it down and saves a run for his team.
Good running. On a length, around off. Crawley is pushed back and he just bunts it out towards covers for a quick single.

Not reviewed! It looked to be missing the bat by a fair way but there was a noise for sure. Starc pitches it up, around off and around 145 kph. The ball just moves away off the pitch and zips past Burns' outside edge. Cummins is the voice of reason from mid on and decides not to review it.Â The replay shows that it didn't hit anything.

As close as it can get to not hitting the stumps. Good-length ball, around off. Burns looks to block it out but ends up chopping it back onto the stumps. The ball though goes a couple of inches over the middle stump and Burns is maybeÂ due for a little bit of luck in this series.
FOUR! Full, sliding on the pads. Burns keeps his balance and clips it behind square on the leg side for a boundary. This is a much better start from the English opening pair.

FOUR LEG BYES! Down the leg side yet again and Starc just isn't getting his line right here. Burns shuffles a bit and looks to flick it fine. The ball comes off the pads and races away into the fine leg fence.
Boland is right on the money! Length ball, landing outside off and coming back in. Zak leaves it with ease though.
Length, on the body. Worked past square leg for one.
Nice and full, on off. Burns blocks it back to the bowler.
On a length, right on the off pole. Burns stays back and defends it.
Boland comes 'round the wickets and bowls it full, just outside off. Burns covers the stumps an leaves it.

A big appeal for LBW! Full ball, around off. Burns stays in the crease to block it out but gets hit on the pads. There is a big appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. The fielders move forward to have a chat. Height is something that is being discussed and they reckon that it might be going over. Not reviewed.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Beaten! Angled into middle from wide of the crease, on a length. It goes away a bit after pitching to beat Crawley's attempted defence.
FOUR! Oh, that is lovely! Length ball, around off. Zak CrawleyÂ takes a step down the track and nicely works it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Two more now! On a length, around off. Zak gets the inside edge wide of deep backward square leg for a couple. Good running there.
Jaffa! Back of a length, just outside off. Zak CrawleyÂ is forced to poke at it but it zips past the outside edge.

FOUR! Cummins strays on the pads and Zak CrawleyÂ punishes it! Full, on middle and leg. A step forward and Crawley flicks it past the diving mid on fielder for a boundary. Highest opening pair for England in the series. These two ave looked reallyÂ good in the middle.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Full, on off. Burns works it past square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Blocked out.
Boland bowls it fuller and wider this time. Zak leaves it for Carey.
Back of a length, around off. Blocked out to cover.
On a length, on the pads. Zak gets rapped on the pads. The ball rolls past square leg and a single is taken.
A length ball, around off. Crawley taps it towards the point region.

FIFTY-RUN STAND! Back of a length, angling into middle and leg. Crawley works it off the back foot towards mid-wicket for a single. A 50-run opening stand for England! This sight has been rare for them to witness in the recent past, but the English fans have something to cheer about now!
Short of a good length, angling across off stump. Burns hops back and keeps it out on the off side.
Slightly fuller, on off. Burns presents the full face of the bat and punches it towards mid off.
A well-directed shortish ball, over middle and just angling across the left-hander. Burns just about sways away from the line of the ball.
On middle, hit on the up towards mid on.

NOT OUT! Full ball, on middle and leg. Zak CrawleyÂ shuffles a bit and looks to flick it. The ball hits the pads and there is a big appeal for LBW! The umpire is unmoved again. Cummins runs in towards the pitch and has a word with his players. One of the players says that height should not be an issue and Cummins takes the review with a second left on the clock. The replays roll in. No bat on that and Ball Tracker has the ball clipping the leg stump with umpire's call! A lucky break for England. Had that been given out on field, the review would not have saved Zak Crawley!
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on the pads. Zak gets hit on the pads and the ball rolls to the leg side. A leg bye is taken by the batters.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Back of a length, just outside off. Burns gets behind the ball to block it.
Nicely pushed to mid off by Burns to end the over.
Tap and run. Length, around off. Zak taps it with soft hands to cover and sets off for a single.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Blocked out.
Snorter! This lands just a touch fuller, just outside off and angling away. Burns looks to block from the crease but is beaten.
Full, on middle. Burns works it through mid on and they get back for the third. Good shot.
Ouch! Short of a length, on off. Zak looks to pull but gets hit on the body.
Length ball, on middle. Flicked past square leg for one.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
On a length, on middle. Worked to short fine leg.
FOUR! Too fine and helped on its way! Full and down the leg side. Zak CrawleyÂ just helps it on its way to the fine leg fence.
Nice and full, on off. Zak blocks it out.
Beaten! Boland drags his length back a bit as Zak CrawleyÂ is batting out of the crease. He also pushes it wider, outside off. Crawley is beaten as he looks to block it away.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller, around off. Burns pushes it towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! Great effort by Marnus LabuschagneÂ but it is a boundary! Length ball, outside off. Burns drives it nicely through covers. Marnus LabuschagneÂ chases it and does so till the end. He puts in a slide to bring it back in. The TV umpire is called in to check though. Replays show that his hand just brushed the boundary padding while he tries to pull it back in. Boundary.
Length, on off. Blocked out.

NOT OUT! What was that noise then? There was a noise for sure but there doesn't seem to any bat on it! Length ball, around off. Burns looks to block but the ball goes past the bat and goes to the keeper. Warner goes up and so does Green. Carey puts in delayed appeal too but the umpire is unmoved. Cummins moves forward and decides to review this one. Now, the replays roll in. First is Hotspot and there is nothing on it. Now, the UltragEdge is a bit interesting. There is a spike but the front-on angle is cropped and the umpire cannot see if there is a deflection to correlate with the UltraEdge spike. The TV umpire goes back to the front-on vision and that shows no clear deflection. He decides that there is no conclusive evidence and the onfield decision stays.
Full, outside off and Burns leans in to punch it towards covers.
On a good length, around off. This is driven nicely but straight to mid off.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
On a length, but wide enough for Zak to leave it with ease.
FOUR! Nicely done! Length, on the pads. Zak CrawleyÂ flicks it nicely to the square leg fence.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Length, around off. Tapped towards gully.
Nice and full, on off. Zak CrawleyÂ comes forward to block it.

OUT! BOWLED! Oh, dear. Oh, dear dear. What has happened there? A session that was dominated by EnglandÂ ends with their opening stand broken! Length ball, just outside off. This comes in with theÂ angle and gets quite close to the off pole. Now, Burns decides to leave it a bit too late and that proves to be his undoing. The ball takes the bottom part of the bat and goes onto hit the stumps! A much-needed wicket for Australia and that is Tea on Day 3!
Howout: b Cameron Green

Commentary: Length ball, right around the top of off. Malan taps it towards covers.
Green goes full and on off. Malan pushes it out towards mid off.
Green pulls back his length a bit and angles it at the body. Malan looks to block but gets caught on the crease and the ball hits him on the arms.
Green bends his back this time and angles in a short ball, at the body. Malan does well to sway away from the line of the ball.

FOUR! Streaky boundary to get off the mark from Dawid MalanÂ but he will take it. Full and outside off, Malan throws his hands at it and manages to squeeze it behind point for a boundary. Under 200 required now to win.
On a good length, over off. Crawley stays solid in defense.
A lovely shot for no run. Pitched up, on middle and the straight drive comes out. Crawley hits it dead straight and hits the stumps on the opposite end.
Length again, around middle. Crawley keeps it out towards mid-wicket.
On a length, around the fifth-stump line. Crawley defends it solidly off the front foot.
On off. Defended towards mid off.
That one moved late. Slightly pitched up, outside off and Crawley makes an assured leave. Maiden over from Scott Boland.
FOUR! Positive intent from Dawid Malan. A length ball, wide of off stump. Malan stands tall and slaps it past the diving fielder at point for a boundary.

Ouch! What a ripper! Green angles in a quick short ball, around the helmet. Dawid MalanÂ just takes his eyes off the ball a bit and gets stung on the grill of the helmet. That one must have shaken up the batter. Luckily it didn't go through the gap inside the grill. Hope he is okay.
Shorter in length again, outside off. Malan makes the leave.
Short and wide, Malan leaves it alone.
Lucky! On a length, around off. Malan looks for the booming cover drive but gets an inside edge past the stumps. The batters get a single as well.
FOUR! Beautiful stroke! Length again, outside off. Zak CrawleyÂ stands tall and creams it through the covers for a boundary.
Around the top of off, Malan blocks it out.
Boland goes full and angles it on off stump. Malan pushes it out towards mid off.
Back of a length, outside off. Malan hangs back and taps it towards point.
Nicely bowled, in that channel around the off stump. Malan shoulders arms.
A bit uppish, but through the gap. Length again, around off and driven on the up towards sweeper cover for a single.
Good-length ball, on off and defended out.
Green is getting a good zip through the surface. Short of a good length, outside off and shaping away a bit. Malan throws his hands at it but misses.
Green is certainly getting the better of Malan out there. On a good length, around off and angling in sharply. Malan gets cut in half and has no answer to that one.
On top of off and Malan stays solid in defense.
A good bumper again, around the off pole. Malan sways away from it.

OUT! Chopped on! Cameron GreenÂ does get the wicket of Dawid MalanÂ and he is elated. Malan was troubled by the short ball and that extra zip that Green is getting off the surface. This is on a good length, close to off stump and just nips back inÂ ever so slightly. Dawid MalanÂ is indecisive and has a late poke at it. His feet don't move and the inside edge is found. The ball goes back onto hit the off stump. Is this the opening the hosts were looking for?
Howout: b Cameron Green

Commentary: Right on the money from Green. Root defends it nicely off the front foot.
A length ball, angled into middle and leg. Crawley keeps it out.
Back of a length, outside off and dabbed down towards short cover.
Lovely away movement again from Boland. Pitched up, a bit wide of the off stump and shaping in. Crawley leaves it alone.
Boland hits the length hard and bowls it on off. Crawley hops back to defend.

LEG BYE! Apart from Joe RootÂ no one knew where that ball went. Length again, outside off. Zak CrawleyÂ shuffles across the stumps and looks to whip it leg side. He misses and the ball goes off his pads towards backward point. They do eventually get a leg bye.
Good-length ball, outside off. Root is outside the crease and is outside the off pole as well. He leaves it alone.
Around the top of middle. Crawley keeps it out on the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Cameron GreenÂ is turning this match on its head all by himself! Green pitches this one up, around off and this one seems to be going on with the angle but just straightens a bit, enough to get the knick. Zak CrawleyÂ is drawn forward and he plays for the line but is undone by the late movement. The ball goes off the outside edge and Alex CareyÂ dives to his right to take a sharp catch. Crawley was looking so good out there and now the visitors are certainly under pressure with two new batters out in the middle.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Cameron Green

Commentary: Back of a length, outside off. Stokes hangs back and steers it through backward point for a single.
Around off, kept out by Root.
Green is making the ball talk here. On a good length, around off and this one nips back in sharply off the surface. Root gets caught on the crease and gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good-length again, on off and angling in. Root gets it off the inner half of the bat towards square leg for one and opens his account.
A length ball, on off. Root hops on the back foot to defend.
Length again, around off and pushing Root back to defend.
Starc drifts onto the pads and Root tickles it towards fine leg for a single.
Beaten! Nicely angled in, around off and the ball just holds its line after pitching. Stokes looks to block but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Shorter in length and well outside off. Stokes isn't going to play at that one.
A sort of half-volley, on middle and leg. Ben StokesÂ flicks it nicely but straight to the fielder at wide mid on.
Green certainly is on song here. A well-directed bumper, on off. Joe RootÂ does well to get his head out of the way in time.
Length this time, around off. Root taps it on the off side.
Good-length ball, on off. This is squeezed to the right of point for a quick single.
On off. Blocked out.
Ouch! This is angled at the bodyÂ from 'round the wicket. Stokes looks to pull but is through his shot early and gets a blow around the ribs.
Length ball, on off and this is pushed towards covers for a run.
Fired full, on the pads. Stokes flicks it past mid on for a couple.
Back of a length, on off. Stokes blocks it from the crease.
A lovely push to mid off for nothing.
On a length, around off. Stokes pushes it nicely to mid off again.
Nice and full, on off. Stokes blocks it out.
Full and down the leg side. Stokes misses the flick.
Short of a length, outside off. Root hops back and pushes it to cover.
Length ball, outside off. Root leaves it alone.
Oh jaffa! Length ball, lands on the off pole. Root has to play and looks to block. The ball nips away a bit and goes past the outside edge.
Full, on off. Root blocks it from the crease.
On a length, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Play and a miss! Short of a length, outside off. Root goes for the cut shot but misses.
Full and on the pads.Stokes flicks it towards deep square leg for one.
Nice and full, around off. Root stays in the crease to block it.
Length ball, lands on off and angles away. Root blocks it towards cover.
A touch shorter and touch wider. Root slaps it towards deep point for one.

OUT! TAKEN! GONE! England in big, big trouble now! A brilliant catch by Lyon and Starc is pumped! He gets the important wicket of Stokes at the right moment for Australia. A surprise bumper, on middle. Stokes goes for the pull but gets the top edge. The ball goes towards deep square leg. Lyon, who hasn't had a lot to do in this game, runs in from the fence. He dives forward and takes a very good catch.
Howout: c Nathan Lyon b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Fuller, around off. Pushed past cover for one.
Bumper, down the leg side. Pope sits under it.
On a length, lands outside off and comes back in. Pope leaves it alone.
Beaten! Perfect delivery. Length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Pope looks to block that from the crease but it holds its line and goes past the outside edge.
Fuller and a bit wider. Left alone.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Pope ducks under it.
Nice and full, on off. Pope stays on the front to block it.
Very full again, around off. Root pushes it to cover.

FOUR! Misfield and a boundary! Length and on off. Root drives it nicely and the man at mid off misfields after diving to his right. The ball tickles to the fence. That brings up 5000 runs as Test captain for Joe Root.
Length, on off. Blocked out.

Short and on the body. Root drops his hands expecting that the ball will go past his shoulder. But it stays a bit low and hits the bottom of the bat. Luckily for him, the ball rolls to the slip cordon.
Short and down the leg side. Pulled down to fine leg for a couple.
Length ball, around off. Root dabs it towards gully and Green moves to his right and stops it. He can do no wrong here!
Length ball, around off. Driven down the ground for a single. 100 up for England with that single.
Short of a length, around off. Root pushes it past gully to get a single.
Length ball, outside off. Pope goes at it with his hands and blocks it.
Short, on off. Pope sits under it.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Beaten again! Cummins bowls it full and just outside off. Pope looks to block it from the crease and the ball zips past the outside edge.
Boland serves a length ball, just outside off. Root takes a step down the track and blocks it.
On a length, lands on off and stays a bit low. Root gets his bat down in time to block. Looks like it hit him low on the bat and he needs to change it.
Play and a miss! Back of a length, outside off. Root goes for the punch but misses.

OUT! BOWLED! Oh, boy. Speechless. Simply speechless. Root has a wry smile on his face and to be honest, there is nothing else he can do. Boland though is over the moon and he can do no wrong in the series. That is a really unfortunate way to get out. Lands on a length, on off and simply does not rise up! It shoots low and goes under the bat as Root is in the crease to block it. It goes onto hit the off pole and Root walks back. Things could get over soon now.
Howout: b Scott Boland

Commentary: Good-length ball, wide of off stump. Billings has a poke at it and edges it down towards gully.
Angled into middle. Billings defends it solidly off the front foot.
On lengh, outside off. Pushed to cover.
Back of a length, outside off. Pope goes back to block but it zips past the outside edge.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
On a length, on off. Pope blocks it out.
Ouch! Short and on off. Pope looks to sway away but does not get low enough. The ball hits his shoulder.
Length ball, around off. Pushed towards gully but Green dives to stop the ball. A big cheer from the crowd.
Length ball, on off. This comes back in. Billings looks to block but gets hit high on the pads.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full, on the pads. Billings looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The ball goes to the leg side and they sneak in a leg bye.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, outside off. Pope gets forward to block it.
Fuller, around off. Pope works it past square leg for a couple.
Short of a length, around off. Blocked out.
Full and on off. Billings gets the outside edge but it rolls towards the slip cordon.
Short of a length, around off. Pushed towards gully.
Short and on off. Pope pulls it to deep square leg for one.
Length and on the pads. Billings gets it off his pads to fine leg for a leg bye.
Back of a length, around off. Blocked out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Soft dismissal for Sam BillingsÂ and EnglandÂ are just crumbling under pressure. A length ball, angling into middle and leg. There is a bit of an extra bounce on offer for Scott BolandÂ and that is what catches Billings out. He doesn't move his feet and is caught on the crease as he flicks it uppishly and straight into the hands of the skipper, Pat CumminsÂ at mid on. It's all but over now for the visitors. Chris WoakesÂ is the new man in.
Howout: c Pat Cummins b Scott Boland

Commentary: Fuller in length, on off. This is pushed towards mid off.
Full again, trying to attack the pads. Woakes drives it towards mid off.
On off. Blocked out.
Back of a length, around off. Woakes takes it eye off the ball and just about manages to get a bat on it.
A length ball, angling into middle. Woakes manages to defend it out.
Around off. Pope tucks it towards short mid-wicket.

OUT! Cleaned up! The last of the recognized batters perishes and AustraliaÂ all over the visitors right now. Pat CumminsÂ hurls across a length ball that is angled into leg stump. Ollie PopeÂ walks right across his stumps as he looks to flick it away. He misses and pays the ultimate price as the ball crashes into leg stump. Just three wickets to go now and England cannot believe it.
Howout: b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Good-length ball, outside off. Wood taps it through covers for a single.
Ooh, a nasty bouncer but Woakes does well. Shorter in length, angled towards the helmet. Woakes somehow manages to get it behind square forÂ a single.
A quick bumper, outside off. Wood has a swipe at it but misses it completely.
Back of a length, around off. Wood hops and works it on the off side for one.
On off, pushed towards covers for a single.
Around off. Blocked.
FOUR! Nicely played. On middle and leg, Woakes flicks it in front of square on the leg side and picks up a boundary.
Back of a length, Woakes opens the face of the bat and guides it towards gully.
Shorter in length, around off and angled in. Woakes looks to hook but doesn't get any bat on it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Edged and taken wonderfully by Alex Carey! Boland goes fuller, around off. Chris WoakesÂ gives himself room and goes for the big heave on the leg side. The ball comes off the outside edge and flies to the right of the keeper. Alex CareyÂ springs and takes a gem of a catch. Woakes perishes and AustraliaÂ just two wickets away now from victory.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Scott Boland

Commentary: FOUR! Wood will go down swinging! Full, outside off. He clears his front leg and slaps it through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! Up and over! Length ball, on off. Wood heaves it over mid off for a boundary.

OUT! BOWLED! Cummins gets his man! Mark WoodÂ knows there's no point in hanging around and looks to go out with a few lusty blows. A short ball, outside off and Wood shuffles across looking to hook it away. The ball hurries onto him and he ends up getting an inside edge back onto the stumps and that's just been the story of this series. The English team just throwing in the towel way too early.
Howout: b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Another short ball, on middle. Broad backs away and plays it towards backward point for a run.

OUT! BOWLED! What a way to end the series as it is the captain, Pat Cummins, whoÂ gets the final wicket and takes his team to victory! Full, fast and dead straight. Ollie RobinsonÂ moves across the leg stump and just has no answer for the yorker. The ball shatters the stumps and AUSTRALIA WIN BY 146 RUNS AND WIN THE ASHES 4-0!
Howout: b Pat Cummins
